{'name': '3 Bedroom / Ocean views / Free Parking - Waikiki', 'neighborhood_overview': 'This hotel is one of the most popular locations in Waikiki because it is so close to the beach and all Waikiki attractions.  It is convenient to everything you will want to see and do during your vacation. Outdoor activities are countless from this location. Restaurants and international shopping are bountiful nearby. Fast food to 5 star dinning is available. Enjoy the unique Kuhio Ave. for dinning and shopping with the locals. Hawaiian food, Hawaiian artifacts and Hawaiian clothing are all available withing walking distance.', 'property_type': 'Apartment', 'bedrooms': 3, 'address': {'street': 'Honolulu, HI, United States', 'suburb': 'Honolulu', 'government_area': 'Primary Urban Center', 'market': 'Oahu', 'country': 'United States', 'country_code': 'US', 'location': {'type': 'Point', 'coordinates': [-157.82805, 21.27983], 'is_location_exact': True}}, 'reviews': [{'comments': 'Everything went smoothly and the apartment was great. The cleanliness and all the small touches, from the bathroom items to the coffee in the kitchen.\r\n\r\nThe apartment complex has an excellent location and great ammenities.'}, {'comments': 'The host canceled this reservation the day before arrival. This is an automated posting.'}, {'comments': 'I stayed here in a group of 10 for 4 nights for a wedding. We were on a tight budget and found the condo great value for money, with amazing views from two large balconies, a very short walk to the center of town, a bus stop right in front of the building, and plenty of towels and linen for use. Mark was also flexible with check in and graciously allowed us to check in very early after a horrible overnight flight which landed at 7am! We were there during a rare storm, however, and the windows in the bedroom with the balcony did not keep the strong winds out completely. Also, the dining table and sofas did not fit all 10 of us. Otherwise, we very much enjoyed our stay and would recommend this condo for other large groups.'}, {'comments': 'Mark的公寓位于Waikiki海滩附近,周边交通很方便,步行5分钟到海滩,3分钟到ROSS,下楼就能看到ABCstore｡\n我们租住的公寓位于35层,客厅和主卧的阳台有很美的风景,早上可以看到东边的日出,晚上可以看到海滩一侧的晚霞｡\n公寓如Mark在bnb上介绍的那样,设施完善,富有艺术气息,整洁方便,客卧的高低床适合有孩子的家庭入住｡\nWaikiki海滩的停车一直是很贵的,但Mark的公寓有地下停车位可以免费使用,真的是非常方便｡\n在Waikiki度假选择Mark的公寓一定没错!'}, {'comments': 'Great location in Waikiki and a wonderful apartment for a larger group. Very comfortable. The included parking space is a real asset.'}, {'comments': '기대하였던 것보다 상당히 좋았기에 이렇게 후기를 남깁니다.\n총 11명이 로얄쿠히오#3507에서 4박하였습니다.\n큰 수건은 약 30여개 정도가 있어서 충분하였고\n세탁기.건조기 도 잘 작동되어서 2시간만에 빨래/건조가 가능 하였습니다.(세제도있었음). 주방에는 접시 냄비 밥솥 등이 full로 갖추어져 있어서 밥을 해먹을수 있었습니다.(가위가 없어서 아쉬었음). 샤워실 세면대에 물이 막혀 내려가지 않앗는데 manager에게 문의 후 5시간만에 빠르게 해결해 주었습니다. 에어콘 작동 잘되고. 인터넷 잘됩니다. 걸어서 3분거리에 무수비가게. 맥도널드,마루카메우동,ABC마트 등등이 있어서 아주 편리합니다. 비행기도착과 동시에 숙소로 향하였고 13:00PM에 checkin을 해주었습니다. 비치의자 5개 있음. 바디보드 없음. 어린이 모래놀이 장난감 1set 있음.\n뷰 좋음.  단점:신발&양말을 벗고 맨발로 바닥을 걸어다녔는데 발바닥이 좀 많이 더러워 졌었습니다. 이에 다른분들께도 추천합니다.'}, {'comments': 'We loved the views, and the comfortable living spaces. Thank you so much Mark, for a wonderful stay. '}, {'comments': "It's good location to the shopping center and beach"}, {'comments': 'Great place to stay with a bunch of friends in Honolulu!'}, {'comments': "Awesome views of mountains, city skyline, city lights, rainbows & ocean. A lot of linens & toiletry provided. If you have more than 1 car though, you will have to find parking elsewhere. There's a Ross down the street that had a parking garage charging $35/day for parking, which is much cheaper than others around the area.\n\nOther than this, everything was great."}, {'comments': 'Great location.'}, {'comments': '와이키키와 가까웠고\n도보로 쇼핑, 식사, 구경을 할수 있었습니다\n오아후의 남동부해안 노쇼어등\n곳곳을 편하게 이동할수있네요'}, {'comments': "This is a roomy condo in a good location with spectacular views of the ocean and the mountains. We had a great time! The condo is clean and well-appointed. We had five adults staying here, and we never felt cramped. The place is well stocked with plenty of linens, including a generous supply of beach towels. The kitchen had plenty of dishes for virtually any cooking need, including a tea kettle and two types of teapots. The building also has a recreation deck with a pool, exercise room, sauna, ping-pong tables and more.\n\nThe check-in process was incredibly easy. We texted the host when we left the airport and were met at the condo by a guest host who showed us around and helped with our bags. In an unexpected complication, one of our party had broken their leg before the trip and was in a wheelchair. We hadn't booked the location with handicap accessibility in mind, but it turned out great. For anyone traveling with mobility issues, this is a good location. With an elevator and ramp out front, the wheelchair was no problem. The bathrooms are a bit too tight for a wheelchair if that's a requirement for you, but that's normal for any place that hasn't been specifically designed to be wheelchair accessible.\n\nThe only downside I'll list is that the foldout couches aren't that great. There are five beds in the bedrooms, but one of our party snores and was going to sleep in the living room on one of the foldout couches. It turned out that the mattress was very thin and after a very short discussion we decided we could wear earplugs because an adult would probably not get a good night sleep on the couches. That said, the five of us slept great in the five beds (two are bunkbeds, but were fine even for adults). The place isn't brand new and has signs of wear around the edges, but no more than one would expect in a vacation property. \n\nOverall, we were very happy with our stay and we'd both recommend it and go back there again!"}, {'comments': '위치뿐만 아니라, 청결도 안전까지 굉장히 좋은 곳이었습니다 :) 중간에 문제를 해결해주시는 것도 아주 빨랐고 좋았습니다 ^^ 없는 게 없을 정도로 완벽했어요 ! 주변에 쇼핑과 먹을 곳이 굉장히 많이 아주 좋았습니다 ! 다음에 또 가고싶을 정도였어요.'}, {'comments': "We have enjoyed Mark's apartment immensely.  All the rooms were clean, well-kept, everything was in working order and well prepared.\n\nThe view of the ocean from the balcony was spectacular and soothing at the same time.  The location was a short walk to the central Wakiki, even my 80+ aged in-laws did not find difficult to walk.\n\nI would highly recommend Mark's place and if you are planning a family get together on Wakiki as I was, give Mark's large apartment a look-in.\n\nCheers from Peter"}, {'comments': "Fantastic place!!! It was way more beautiful that the pictures posted. The A/C worked great in all the rooms (which is what we needed), absolutely LOVED the Guest bathroom shower. Perfect location. Never used my car, walked everywhere we needed to go. Also an ABC Store, Starbucks, and a McDonald's either literally across the street or a block away. Will DEFINITELY request this room for our next Staycation in Waikiki. Thanks, Mark!!!"}, {'comments': 'So we actually got upgraded to a different room d/t some plumbing issues #3506 so this review will be that room. \n\nLocation was fantastic, right in the middle of where you want to be. About 5-min walking distance to the beach. The place was spotless and the ocean view from the bedroom with the double beds was absolutely incredible.\n\nThe place had a sofa bed, an ottoman that turned into a single bed, and extra blankets/bedding in the closets. \n\nThe place was very comfortable, felt like Home. The second bedroom with the full bed and bunk beds was very comfortable as well, it’s just a bit cramped as there isnt much space other than the beds and a small closet. But we were able to store luggage under the beds which helped, and not to take away from how great this place is, just to give an idea of what the room is like.\n\nHowever there are so many other options for sleeping such as the two beds in the living room plus extra mats/bedding in the closet so if the one room feels cramped there is plenty other space to either sleep or store luggage.\n\nThis place would be perfect for a bigger family and even has items there for a baby like a high chair and some other things too.\n\nThere were also boogie boards on one of the balconies which was very nice to have.\n\nOverall I️ highly recommend this space, and I️ actually wish I️ had the chance to stay and relax in the room more because I️t was really that nice and comfortable.'}, {'comments': 'Mark was great to work with and responded very quickly. He was sure to get in contact if there was anything he needed.'}, {'comments': 'The apartment was great for our family group of two teenagers, a five year old, and two adult.\nWell situated for beach, shopping and restaurants.'}, {'comments': 'Good location and service!'}, {'comments': 'This apartment is fabulous. The views are spectacular, it was clean and nicely decorated. There was a booklet with tons of great local information. The AC was much needed. I would recommend this place if you want to be right in the heart of Honolulu and Waikiki. Shopping and Restaurants are right there, bus system is everywhere, there\'s 1 free garage parking space that fits 6\'5" and under. The check in process was easy and fast.'}, {'comments': 'This apartment is incredible! Two balconies with breathtaking views, full kitchen, two bathrooms and TVs in every room. We all had our own space and not to mention access to all hotel facitilies. Great communication with our host and great location. Can’t recommend this apartment enough. '}, {'comments': '立地は抜群です｡\nﾄｲﾚｯﾄﾍﾟｰﾊﾟｰや洗剤など買い足す必要があるが大きな問題なし｡\n大人数での旅行に最適｡'}, {'comments': '家族で利用しましたが､個室とﾘﾋﾞﾝｸﾞの数がちょうど良くとても快適に過ごせました｡皆んなも喜んでました｡\n眺めも最高だし､立地も中心に位置する為どこ行くにも良い所でした!!!\nまたﾊﾜｲに行った時は利用したいです!!!'}, {'comments': "location,view,facilities were very good.\nThe House is suitable for family.\n3 room's beds were very comfortable. \nIt is located close to famous points.\nOur family whole members were satisfied."}, {'comments': 'The rental was in an ideal location and was within walking distance to anything you’ll need in Waikiki. There was ample space in the condo, even for 8 guests. Wished there was a second parking space available in the garage, but aside from that, it was an excellent stay. Would definitely stay here again!'}, {'comments': 'Super convenient location, amazing view. Friendly guest host (we had Alex) who gave great explanations. We had a great time. Thank you!!'}, {'comments': '10/10. Great location. Amazing view.'}, {'comments': 'It was wonderful airbnb near Waikiki and downtown! Definitely recommended!'}, {'comments': '집 위치는 와이키키 해변까지 걸어서 5분? 정도이고 주변 쇼핑 거리와도 매우 가까워서 위치는 매우 만족스럽다. \n총 6명이서 함께 지냈는데 불편한거 하나없이 널널하게 생활했고, 특히 거실과 방안에서 밖에 보이는 view 가 끝내준다.\n다만 예약확정 되고 난 후에 몇시에 로비에서 만날건지 먼저 물어보고 꼭 확답을 받아낼것..!\n이걸 안해서 당일날 부랴부랴 전화했었음.\n집을 보여준 Mark인지 누구인지 모르겠지만 (이름을 못 물어본게 아쉽다) 너무 친절했고, 감사했다'}, {'comments': 'Beautiful, exceptional condominium with million dollar viewsParking, security and all the amenities! We didn’t want to leave❤️'}], 'score': 0.7125971913337708}
{'name': '2br/1ba,1 kitchentte, 10min walk to Waikiki beach', 'neighborhood_overview': '', 'property_type': 'Apartment', 'bedrooms': 2, 'address': {'street': 'Honolulu, HI, United States', 'suburb': 'Oʻahu', 'government_area': 'Primary Urban Center', 'market': 'Oahu', 'country': 'United States', 'country_code': 'US', 'location': {'type': 'Point', 'coordinates': [-157.82304, 21.27703], 'is_location_exact': True}}, 'reviews': [{'comments': 'I booked this place for my friend and her family for the first time in Honolulu.  They liked the location, very close to beaches and shops and restaurant.  But they wonder why they had to take the trashes down after paying the cleaning fees.   '}, {'comments': '房东非常热心周到负责｡房子非常干净舒适,甚至好于图片｡'}, {'comments': "친구들과 함께한 청춘여행 8일중 4일을 여기서 지냈는데 가성비 최고의 숙소이다. 호스트인 카즈에씨는 출국 이전부터 세심하게 체크인 시간이며 궁금한 점이 있는지 확인했으며 메세지를 남기면 곧장 답장이왔다. 하와이에 도착하고 약속한 체크인 시간보다 다소 늦었으나 호스트는 진작에 숙소에서 기다리고 있었다.(전반적으로 일관되게 굉장히 친절하게 설명해주고 궁금한 점을 해결해주었다)  이 방은 다소 연식이 있어보이는 아파트 4층에 있으며 유일한 단점은 계단을 이용해야 한다는 것이다.(가벼운 운동한다고 생각하면 무리 없다.) 방으로 들어가니 최근에 인테리어를 해서 그런지 낡은 아파트와는 반대로 다소 깔끔하고 세련된 모습을 하고 있었다. 무엇보다 기대이상으로 깔끔하게 관리되어온 모습이 마음을 굉장히 편하게 만들어 주었다. 호스트가 워낙 꼼꼼한 분이셔서 부족한 것이 하나 없이 구비되어 있던 생활용품이 호텔보다 훨씬 훌륭했다. 이 방에서 4일간 지내면서 가장 큰 장점 두가지를 꼽으라면 깔끔함과 모든 것이 완비되어 있는 것이었다.  총평으로는 굉장히 만족스러웠다. 가성비가 뛰어나다. 특히 친구들끼리 오는 여행객들에게 적극 추천해주고 싶다.\r\n\r\nFor 4days I've spent fabulous time with my friends. The host, Kazue san was very precise, friendly and kind. She double checked our check-in time to be on time and asked us if we have any questions even before we arrive at Hawaii. The room was spacious and extremely clean. Also interior was fancy.(totally different with the exterior of the building) Beds was comfortable enough to solve our tiredness from tight trip schedules and everything in this apartment was well-prepared. The best two advantages of this apartment are cleaness and Well-stocked daily supplies. Thanks to the host for making us feel and live like one of the local Hawaiians. I would defenetly stay in her place again if I have another chance to go to Hawaii!!"}, {'comments': "Kazue was very accommodating as soon as we got to the location.\nAs soon as we walked in, she gave us a detailed tour of the house and the location.\n\nShe as well had extra amenities for us to last the whole week, if not extra being provided.\n\nKazue was a great host and anyone wanting a close home by the beach should definitely go ahead with kazue's airbnb. :)"}, {'comments': 'great location, nice place, great host..... '}, {'comments': "1. Great location\r\n\r\n2. Enough room for 4 guests with 4 beds\r\n\r\n3. Easy to check-in & check-out\r\n\r\n4. Easy to park a rent-car with extra pay by US$15 cash a day\r\n\r\n5. Bad noise from outside and air conditioners inside\r\n\r\n6. Don't expect any views through windows\r\n\r\n7. It's good for guests who spend most of their time outside till late night"}, {'comments': 'The appartement ist clean, good street - calm  and reale near to Waikiki.'}, {'comments': "I went to Honolulu for the Honolulu marathon with my parents and my brother. We stayed at Kazue's place because it is close to the finish line. It turned out to be a convinient location for everything else. \nWe liked our stay and the host Kazue and John were so kind and friendly. We felt very welcoming.\nWe had a good time in Honolulu thanks to Kazue and John. Thank you!"}, {'comments': '정말 깔끔하고 좋았습니다! 다만 음식을 만드는 레인지가 살짝 열이 부족해서 음식을 빨리빨리 만들지 못했네요, 가족과 가시는 분이나 음식을 사먹지않고 하시는 분이라면 가스레인지를 하나 사시는 걸 추천합니다!'}, {'comments': '친구들과 2일 동안 편안하게 잘 머물렀어요. \n와이키키까지 걸어갈 수 있는 가까운 거리, 별이 잘 보이던 옥상, 산책이나 조깅을 할 수 있던 운하길, 간단한 식사를 할 수 있던 자그마한 주방이 좋았어요.\n아쉬웠던 점은 화장실 세면대의 물이 조금씩 나왔고 우리는 4명이었는데 테이블 의자가 3개 밖에 없어서 좀 불편했어요.\n'}, {'comments': 'We enjoyed our stay at this place as it is very conveniently located in Waikiki. It was very easy to communicate with Kazue and she was very accommodating to our need\n'}, {'comments': "Kazue is a good host and very supportive. \nThe location is fine and not too far from the Waikiki beach.\nThis place is recommended for young people who just need a place to sleep and don't care about noise come from the airco or outside. \nThe 4th floor without elevator can be an issue if you do shopping a lot in Honolulu.\nThanks Kazue for your support during our stay there!"}, {'comments': '房子里海滩很近,每天晚上我们都走路去海滩,很方便｡The apt is very close to the beach, every night we walk to the beach, very convenient. Our plane was dalay, but the John has been waiting for us to 1:30 am to open the door, very grateful.'}, {'comments': 'The location is very convenient: an ideal place for people who want to spend time at the beach. It is close to all dining options as well.'}, {'comments': 'Beds were really quite comfortable. Kitchen was perfect with all the basics needed to make our stay comfortable. Location was perfect for getting to all the activities we did. Great place, great stay and would definitely recommend this to others.'}, {'comments': 'It was good ! Really close to evrything . For this price it is really good. WiFi is not sooo good But that was Okay ! We had te best time ever'}, {'comments': 'Everything was ok. In spite there was no elevator they help us with the luggage very kindly. Is an apartment with a very good ubication, near waikiki beach. We enjoy a lot. '}, {'comments': "What a great place to stay! I took my parents and my family to Hawaii for the first time, with little toddler and two family, we were struggling to find a suitable accommodation in the primary location. This place was nice, clean, best location in Waikiki. Short walk to shops, beach and bus stops. I found most of bus go through Kuhio ave, so it's super convinient. \n\n"}, {'comments': 'Great time'}, {'comments': "Kazue's place is walking distance to everything in Waikiki, and only a few blocks from the beach. It isn't fancy but it was a great price, and I was very happy with my choice when I stayed here."}, {'comments': 'Kazue is very easy to talk with. Fast response and helpful. The room is clean and convince. The location is just perfect for visitors specially for people want to hang out in Waikiki. \nI highly recommend her place for visiting Hawaii.'}, {'comments': "Good location to stay.\nThe room is top floor on corner.\nWe had a good time on a big terrace, like a Hawaiian!\nI'd love to go again!!\n"}, {'comments': '室内は可もなく不可もなく､清掃は行き届いており不満はありません｡ｱﾒﾆﾃｨやﾄﾞﾗｲﾔｰなどもあり､生活には困りません｡ただ4ﾍﾞｯﾄに4名で宿泊したが､ﾘﾋﾞﾝｸﾞには椅子が2脚しかなく､4名でゆっくりするｽﾍﾟｰｽはない｡あくまで寝るｽﾍﾟｰｽという印象｡\n外に広々としたﾃﾗｽのような共用ｽﾍﾟｰｽがあるのはよかった｡特にﾀﾊﾞｺを吸う人には｡'}, {'comments': '清潔な部屋でした｡\n食器やｺｯﾌﾟも揃っていました｡\nﾊﾞｽﾀｵﾙがいっぱいあったので海に行く時などにも持っていけました｡\nﾎﾞﾃﾞｨｿｰﾌﾟとﾘﾝｽｲﾝｼﾞｬﾝﾌﾟｰもありました｡\n場所も買い物に行くのにもｻﾞ･ﾊﾞｽに乗るにも便利な場所です｡\nABCｽﾄｱも近くにありました｡\n一点､冷蔵庫に今まで部屋を利用した人たちの残り物らしきものがいろいろあったのが少し気になりました｡｡\n'}, {'comments': 'Very kind and reactive host. The condo is very clean (but a bit small for a family, no room to be together). Is is very well situated in Waikiki, not far from everything you want!\n'}, {'comments': 'Definitely would stay again on a future Waikiki visit! Spot is as advertised in the photos. Nothing glamorous but very clean, phenomenal location (walking distance to everything), and Kazue (and John) were extremely communicative. \n\nWifi is not extremely strong FYI, had trouble doing high bandwidth work (though worked fine for email, etc).'}, {'comments': 'Highly recommend house! Clean, big enough, near main street and beach, silent and more:)'}, {'comments': 'Overall a good deal for the price. Very conveniently located, only 3 blocks from Waikiki beach. Our host met us at check-in and was very friendly and responsive when we reached out. There are two bedrooms and no living room which made it a little difficult to hang out together. Good if you just need a convenient place to sleep and prepare simple meals. Only electric hot plates were provided, there were no burners on the stove. The kitchen was well stocked enough for light cooking. Bathroom was clean and plenty of towels and toiletries were provided. The wifi was slow but worked for light browsing.'}, {'comments': 'ｽﾃｷな思い出ができました!ありがとうございます!'}, {'comments': "Kazue's place was great! Very modest, but that was just fine - we didn't visit Waikiki to stay inside all day! It is two air-conditioned bedrooms with two single beds in each, and one bathroom at the end of the hallway/kitchenette combination connecting everything. We tried pushing two beds together to make a double, but they were slightly different heights so it didn't work. There is a nice fridge/freezer, and a stovetop if you wanted to do simple cooking in the kitchenette/hallway, although with so many amazing food options within walking distance, we didn't bother. \n\nThe location is great - walking distance to everything in Waikiki. And the convenience of also being able to rent a parking space helped out tremendously. We rented an affordable car from Turo (use link (Website hidden by Airbnb) for $25 free credit) to explore the island, as Lyft/Uber were surprisingly expensive. I would highly recommend taking advantage of the great parking space and getting a car - Waikiki is one of the many amazing places on Oahu, so give yourself the chance to explore.\n\nI would highly recommend this place if your primary goal is a comfortable place to sleep. If you're looking for a luxury resort room, go to the Sheraton. If you're looking for a modest place to sleep each night, this cozy two bedroom with four single beds in the heart of Waikiki is absolutely the perfect place. Thanks for the great experience, Kazue!"}, {'comments': 'Kazue is a nice and kind host. She made every effort in ensuring a smooth checkin and stay experience. Her apartment is close to the downtown and beach area. We enjoyed our stay very much. Thanks Kazue! :)'}, {'comments': 'とにかくｱｸｾｽもよく､日本語でも対応してくださるので､安心してｽﾃｲすることが出来ました｡\n\nｷｯﾁﾝもある程度整っているので､外食続きが苦手なわたしにはﾋﾟｯﾀﾘでした｡\n\n何よりﾁｪｯｸｲﾝの際に立ち会ってくれた方がとても親切で､楽しい方でしたので､良い旅のｽﾀｰﾄを切ることが出来ました!\n\n感謝です｡'}, {'comments': "Great location at walking distance of everything in Waikiki and public transports,, good price and 2 separate bedrooms exactly what we needed! The host is nice and can be flexible on check-in and check-out when it's possible. Had a great time!"}, {'comments': 'Accomodations were excellent! listing was exactly as listed...would stay again in the future'}, {'comments': 'Great place. John was easily reachable and answered all my questions in a timely manner. Little touches like the bottle of aloe gel in the fridge were a nice touch. The place was as described. Would book and stay again. There is no elevator so be prepared to carry your stuff up 3 flights of stairs.'}, {'comments': 'clean and neat.'}, {'comments': 'Great place close to everything, and good price!!'}, {'comments': "Kazue and John's place was nice, clean, and well located. John gave us help getting our substantial amount of luggage upstairs and gave great advice on local attractions. The apartment has a nice terrace area to kick back with a drink after a day of work or relaxation. Additionally it is located extremely close to Waikiki beach park, Diamondhead, and the Hawaii convention center. The central common space doesn't have AC but the rooms have fantastic window units. Check in and check out were a breeze compared to many other Air BnBs I have stayed at since John and Kazue have it down to a science. This place is truly better than advertised. "}, {'comments': 'Great Location! An easy walk to the beach, restaurants, and bars.'}, {'comments': 'Great location for the price!'}, {'comments': 'La experiencia ha sido buena, John encantador, la ubicación perfecta, deberían renovar algunas cosas.'}, {'comments': "Kazue and John are amazing hosts! Kazue is very responsive to our queries and really nice, they allowed us to check-in early which we greatly appreciate. John is also exceptional, check-in was so smooth (he helped us with our luggage) and he gave us great advice on Honolulu!\n\nGreat location (a lot of things are accessible and the place is easy to find) and the area is safe. Great value for your money! I can't wait to be back in Honolulu and stay again in their place."}, {'comments': 'Kazueさんのﾚｽﾎﾟﾝｽも早くよかったです!\nﾜｲｷｷﾋﾞｰﾁからの立地も良くさい最高でした!'}, {'comments': 'Location is near by the beach and all the action is. But the place need a lot of upgrade, I guess you get what you paid for, so make sure you are getting a good price.'}, {'comments': "My family of 4 had a very nice time at this apartment over Christmas/New Years. It's a top-floor corner apt, so it was generally nice and quiet. The AC is a bit loud, but it's fine if you turn it on Low. It's a great place to come home to after a day out exploring the island, but it's a bit small to spend an afternoon there relaxing. There is no living room, and the kitchen/eating space is small. But none of that really mattered to us. We were able to cook a nice egg breakfast every morning, and head out into the the busy Waikiki neighborhood (really crowded!), explore the island, eat dinner out (make reservations! Or try your luck at the Duke's restaurants, some of which don't take reservations), and come back to a quiet apartment. Plenty of hot water, and great water pressure. We loved that there were four separate beds, all comfortable. Our host Joyce was very responsive and attentive."}, {'comments': 'Incredible value five minute walk to the beach, 4 beds, kitchen and safe.'}, {'comments': 'Kazue’s place was located in an easily accessible place to Waikiki’s main attractions. Communication was prompt and clear and John helped kindly with our check-in process.'}, {'comments': 'Kazue and John are very friendly and responsive. John helped us carry the baggages on to the apartment and provided us a lot of local tips. Flexible check in time, very smooth and easy check-in process.\n\nThe place is generally good. Convenient location and reasonable price. The neighborhood is a little noisy. The WiFi and cooktop are slow, made it a bit hard for us to do work on computer or cook meals.'}, {'comments': "Kazue's place was close to Waikiki beach area and the center. If you want a affordable place to stay and eat out some this place was perfect. Also there are two bedrooms so if you want some privacy its nice too.  Enough kitchenware as well to cook easy meals!\nCons were,  you can hear the next door neighbor if the windows are open, wifi was poor and slow. Three people using internet for work or personal reasons was stressful."}, {'comments': 'Such a good location for a stay in Waikiki! Pretty basic but has everything you need and the beds were relatively comfortable too :) the bedrooms don’t currently have curtains which was our main issue, but other than that it was a great stay!'}, {'comments': 'ﾜｲｷｷからも近く､動物園や水族館にも徒歩で行けます｡\nﾎﾃﾙのように部屋でのんびりするのではなく､日中はほとんど外に出て､部屋に寝に帰るだけと言う人には十分だと思います｡ﾎﾃﾙよりはずいぶん安く宿泊できると思います｡'}], 'score': 0.7071605920791626}
{'name': '2 BR Queen Size Sunny - Nolita', 'neighborhood_overview': "The apartment is right next door to beautiful Old St. Patrick's Cathedral and perfectly situated with access to ALL subway lines making it easy to get anywhere in this fabulous city. Supermarkets & Whole Foods nearby as well as cafes and other places to eat and drink. Literally right above Emporio which is a Michelin rated restaurant.", 'property_type': 'Apartment', 'bedrooms': 2, 'address': {'street': 'New York, NY, United States', 'suburb': 'Manhattan', 'government_area': 'Nolita', 'market': 'New York', 'country': 'United States', 'country_code': 'US', 'location': {'type': 'Point', 'coordinates': [-73.99449, 40.72182], 'is_location_exact': True}}, 'reviews': [{'comments': 'A colleague and I stayed for two weeks and the apartment worked wonderfully for us. Nicely located and Brendan made everything very easy.'}, {'comments': 'The apartment is fantastic - a wonderful location with great bars and restaurants on the doorstep, it looks great and has everything we needed including 2 proper double BRs. Brendan was a brilliant host - very quick at replying to any question we had and really helpful. A great experience all round. '}, {'comments': 'BEST NYC HOLIDAY EVER!!! We stayed in Brendan flat for 5 days at the end of March and cannot fault our host or his flat. From the moment we made the booking, Brendan has been unbelievably helpful pointing us in the right direction to make the most of our time in NYC. His warm and well appointed apartment is perfectly located, you could not ask for a more eclectic mix of restaurants, bars, bakeries and shops. Cherry on the cake there are 3 subway stations minutes away in case you are not an uber traveller. 5 star experience all- round.'}, {'comments': 'Lovely apartment in a great location! Brendan was very helpful and flexible throughout. Highly recommended!'}, {'comments': "Brendan was a great host!  He was very accommodating, and responded very quickly by text.  We met Brendan in the restaurant on the ground floor of his apartment, and walked us through everything.  The size of the apartment was perfect for our group of two couples with two small babies.  Of note, his place is a third floor walkup, which didn't bother us but could be an issue for others.\r\nThe location couldn't be better - in the heart of the village...wonderful shops, restaurants, coffee shop across the street, minutes away from Little Italy and Chinatown, and two blocks from the subway station.  We are already talking about when we will be returning for our next NYC visit.  "}, {'comments': 'Great flat, superb location and Brendan was very helpful. Can thoroughly recommend!'}, {'comments': 'The aparment was great and the location was very good also. It was clean and everything worked. I definetely recommend it.'}, {'comments': 'This is a great apartment in a great location! It is a perfect home base to explore all of NYC. Brendan is a wonderful host and flexible even when our schedule changed. I will book again when I return.'}, {'comments': "Brendan est un hôte attentionné qui s'assure que tout soit bien prêt pour accueillir ses invités. Toujours disponible et prompt à répondre aux questions, c'était un stress en moins que de préparer le voyage et d'arriver à New York pour 10 jours.\r\nSon appartement est vraiment confortable, bien équipé et vraiment bien situé dans Nolita, un quartier de Manhattan fourmillant d'activité le soir et donc propice aux sorties. L'appartement est d'ailleurs situé juste au dessus d'un excellent restaurant : L'Emporio.\r\nJe recommande vivement !"}, {'comments': 'Brendan was super accommodating and a very helpful host. Even before arriving, he was very responsive and helpful when we had any questions about the place. His place is very nice and clean, and close to many subway stations. There are a ton of good cafes, bars, and restaurants close by as well. We would definitely book again with Brendan if we do come back to New York again.'}, {'comments': 'Brendan was the perfect host!  His apartment was exactly as pictured.  It was large (by NYC standards), clean and very comfortable.  He was quick to respond to all communications.  He was also friendly and flexible.  I would stay there again if I find myself in NYC in the future!'}, {'comments': 'Brendam nos ofreció su casa como si fuéramos amigos y nos hizo sentir como en casa. Un buen anfitrión!!\r\n'}, {'comments': 'Really dice location, matching the expectations. A lot of nice restaurants around with the subway just around the corner,'}, {'comments': "As advertised - great neighborhood, very central to all points in the city. The apartment was clean, the meet-up was easy, the owner professional. The apartment is located on the 4th floor of a walk-up, which is pretty normal for nyc. Just something to be aware of in the event that you aren't comfortable with stairs for any reason."}, {'comments': "We loved staying at Brendan's place in Nolita.   The neighborhood is terrific - we enjoyed the cupcake bakery, wine bar, and hipster coffee shop right on our block!  The apartment worked out great, no complaints, Brendan made the check in/out process smooth. We would definitely rent this apartment again."}, {'comments': "We truly had amazing time in New York during stay in Brendan's apartment. Location was perfect. Everything was as advertised. Unfortunately we were not able to meet Brendan in person but he was in contact with us through airbnb so everything went smoothly. All in all if we go back we would choose again Brendan's apartment. Great experience all together :)"}, {'comments': 'great location! we loved the neighborhood, excellent place for visit NY, clean and beautiful apartment. Brendan was very helpful and easy to locate when we needed. Highly recommended.'}, {'comments': 'Stor fleksibilitet i forhold til ind og udtjekning'}, {'comments': 'Appartement bien et confortable, bien situé à manathan dans un quartier bien sympa, métro à proximité... À recommander '}, {'comments': "We had a great stay at Brendan's apartment. It's a roomy apartment and looks just like the pictures. We loved the neighborhood, very cute with lots of little shops and no trouble catching cabs or walking to the subway. Brendan was very courteous, met us outside and was available and easy to communicate with throughout our stay. The apartment was clean and well kept. The only thing I would say is that remember that it is up three flights of stairs. Some of the people I went with hadn't read the listing well and were surprised, but it didn't bother me. Thank you so much Brendan!"}, {'comments': "We had a great time staying in Brendan's apartment. location is perfect and he was flexible with picking up the key. \r\nApartment was clean And has  air conditioning which we really needed in warm and humid NY.\r\nOnly min was that there were only 4 towels for 4 persons for a stay of 5 days and that is not enough, same goes for glasses only 4! "}, {'comments': 'Nice apartment.\r\nGreat location.\r\nClose to restaurants, and the subway.\r\nBrendan was very friendly.\r\nHe offered to store our luggage the day we checked out, witch gave us 1 extra day in NYC :o)\r\n\r\n'}, {'comments': 'Brendan is a very helpfull host, présent at 2 AM to open the door and sent the postcards ! the flat is very well located in NY, Nolita is the place to be but it is noisy and one bedroom has no blinds and we were 3 but There were 2 chairs.'}, {'comments': "L'appartement est idéalement situé au cœur de Nolita, quartier très vivant et très sympathique.\r\nNous avons apprécié les deux chambres séparées parfaites pour 4 adultes.\r\n"}, {'comments': 'Brendan is a fantastic host. He was quite accommodating and flexible around checking in and out. The apartment itself was in a charming area with easily accessible transprotation, was clean and quite sizeable for NYC standards. I would definitely recommend it to any groups traveling through the city.'}, {'comments': 'The apartment was perfect and Brendan was a great host - very responsive and organised. Thanks, we had a great time! '}, {'comments': "Great location, very cute place, nicely decorated.  Typical New York walk up.  We were moving my son into NYU and had a lot of luggage.  Walking up three flights of stairs was a bit of a challenge but once in the place, it's very comfortable and well appointed.  Would have been fine if we didn't have so much baggage.  Brenden is a good host and had left helpful instructions."}, {'comments': 'Wir haben dieses Appartment im trendigen Stadtteil Nolita für uns als Familie (2 Erwachsene, 2 Teenager) für 3 Nächte gemietet. Die Gegend ist toll. Restaurants, Bars und Shops - alles in der Nähe. Brendan hat uns einen Late-Arrival sowie Late-Checkout möglich gemacht, so dass wir sehr viel von unserem Aufenthalt hatten. Die Wohnung ist aufgrund der 2 Schlafzimmer sehr gut für 4 Personen geeignet. Brendan hat immer sofort auf Anfragen reagiert und auch unser in der Wohnung vergessenes Handy an zentraler Stelle hinterlegt, so dass wir es wieder abholen konnten. Es war sehr warm in NYC, aber die Klimaanlage hat sehr gut funktioniert. Die zentrale Lage bedingt allerdings auch, dass das Schlafzimmer zur Straße nicht ganz ruhig ist. Aber dafür ist man schließlich auch in Manhattan.'}, {'comments': 'Brendan was an amazing host and had the whole apartment set up before we arrived. I flew in on a redeye and Brendan had the keys ready for me to pickup. The apartment is roomy by NYC standards and there was more than enough room for 4 of us. Nolita is an amazing neighborhood with enough restaurants and bars to visit for a year; plenty of shopping too. The apartment is located on a quiet enough street with central access to 6 and B,D,F,M trains '}, {'comments': "The apartment is located in a busy and vibrant part of Little Italy and is close to a number of the subway lines. The apartment itself has enough room to use as a place to crash of a night but you fill find that you don't end up spending much time there with everything that is on offer on your doorstep."}, {'comments': "In a city where shoe-box hotel rooms are the norm, this place was a nice fit for my work colleague and myself for three days. The apartment is clean, beds and couch are comfortable and having a kitchen is nice even if we didn't use it during our stay. \r\nBrendan greeted us and walked us up to the flat, and was great at communicating to set up our check-in and stay.  Being on the Lower East Side, right next to Little Italy, it was a short commute downtown, and easily accessible to take the subway to Midtown. Would recommend and stay again. "}, {'comments': "Our host was responsive and helpful. The apartment was exactly as described! Plenty of room for 4 adults, full bath, clean linens, comfortable beds. Air conditioning in both bedrooms made for a great night's sleep. The best part for us was location, Location, LOCATION! This apartment is in a fantastic neighborhood with restaurants and shopping. But it's access to everywhere from Brooklyn to Soho to nearby subways that can take you where ever you need to go; made it perfect. We'll definitely stay here again!"}, {'comments': "Perfect location and lovely little flat! We'll sure be back!!"}, {'comments': 'We have enjoyed our 2 weeks stay at Brendan’s place a lot. He is a good host and keeps his promises.\r\nNolita is a great neighbourhood close to Chinatown and Little Italy with lots of coffee bars, cafes, restaurants, supermarket and metro line at walking distance.\r\nThe apartment offers not  a lot of  space in the living room and kitchen for 4 persons but do not forget that you are in New York City. There is television set available which is great in case of a rainy day and the 2 bedrooms give enough room for 4 persons. In summer time the aircondition offers a great welcome when it is getting too hot inside and the wifi connection works perfect.\r\nHis place we can recommend strongly to anyone who plans to visit New York. \r\n'}, {'comments': "Great stay at Brendan's place in Nolita. Great location, very clean, and place looks exactly like the pictures. Bars, restaurants, and coffee all just steps away. Fantastic Italian restaurant a few floors below the apartment. 4 male adults in one place for 3 nights and it was perfect for NYC standards. Brendan was always very responsive and also accommodated our odd check in/check out times. Subway near by. Couldn't hear other neighbors, and though there was construction going on outside, the noise from that was only during the day. I would use his place again no question. "}, {'comments': 'Service was prompt and the apartment was fantastic!  Location was key.  Would stay again.  Thanks Brendan!'}, {'comments': 'We had a lot of fun in NYC, cause his apt is amazing ,comfortable and more convenient for traffic. We will have his apt and be his guest again without any question. '}, {'comments': 'Nice flat! The nolita hood is one of the best place to stay and to visit NYC! A lot of restaurants bars surrounded by subway stops...a perfect place. Brendan was here for the check in and stay flexible for the check out time! He answered us in a quick manner to all of our questions or requests. So if you r 4 peoples looking for a great stay in NYC i have to recommend you to get in touch with him!'}, {'comments': 'Apartamento aconsejable, en el centro de la ciudad, cerca de la zona financiera de Manhattan. Quzá un poco pequeño, pero teniendo en cuenta que solo era para dormir y poco más, cumple su función a la perfección, el trato con Brendan fue perfecto, incluso nos permitió dejar las maletas en otro apartamento el día que dejamos el piso.\r\n\r\nMuy recomendable para visitar la ciudad, muy bien ubicado.'}, {'comments': "We had a great time at Brendan's 2 bedroom apartment. He was very accommodating to our party. When we arrived a few hours before check in, and he allowed us to temporarily store our bags so we could get our vacation started. And, he helped us store our bags on the way out if the city too.\n The place is in my favorite part of New York, with tons of restaurants, bars and shopping nearby. I would defiantly stay there again. "}, {'comments': 'Muy buena descripción de lo céntrico y de la organización del departamento. Tuvimos todas las facilidades por parte de Brendan.\r\nEl ambiente de los vecinos, y la buena localización del departamento nos ayudó a poder conocer muy bien la ciudad de New York.'}, {'comments': "Brendans' apartment is great! Located in one of the most interesting neighbourhoods in Manhattan with plenty of shops, bars and restaurants nearby. In addition to this, there is a very good subway connection within 5min walking distance.\r\n\r\nWe've been there for a week with four people and the apartment was big enough for us!\r\n\r\nGreat stay, totally recommend it!"}, {'comments': 'Brendan has a very nice apt. within a wonderful neighbourhood. You are very close to everything. The rooms look like displayed at the pictures and the apt. has everything you need for the day. The wifi is pretty good. We have been there with two couples and are completely satisfied.\r\n\r\nTip to travellers: If you get to nyc the first time you can use the free wifi in the subway to contact brendan.\r\n'}, {'comments': 'Great experience. Fantastic location and clean space.'}, {'comments': 'Great staying in the best area. Brendan is super nice and flexibable!'}, {'comments': 'Apt was great, Brendan made it easy and was flexible on check in/out times. I would definitely stay there again. Awesome location! '}, {'comments': 'Brendan was great with communication and responded promptly to all questions and messages. We got to NY early, so Brendan allowed us to store our bags at his place until the apartment was ready, and even gave us some tips on great restaurants. Cafe Habana is awesome! He even let us have a late check out. The apartment was clean, spacious, and best of all, quiet. Everything we needed was there and the location cannot be beat! Would definitely recommend!'}, {'comments': "Four of our friends stayed in Brendan's apartment during Christmas. The apartment is very true to its pictures, clean and comfortable and the neighborhood is great with so many nice restaurants and shops. I would totally recommend this apartment. "}, {'comments': "Great apartment in a great neighborhood, really close to the subway, chinatown and little italy.  Can't go wrong!"}, {'comments': 'We much appreciated the contact with Brendan right from the start. He was very easy to communicate with. The appartment was terrific and the location excellent. We had splendid days in NY, and I could well imagine returning to this flat on my next visit.'}, {'comments': "Super appartement! Comme dans la description. On a passé un super moment là-bas. Un point de départ de très bonne qualité pour sillonner New York.\r\n\r\nBrendan nous a donné les clés et nous a dit ''Vous êtes chez vous''! Juste parfait et réactif par texto.  \r\n\r\nMerci Brendan"}, {'comments': 'Brendan was a terrific host from start to finish.  He was quick to reply,  very accommodating and helpful.  The description was spot on (clean and comfortable) and the location was terrific for our needs.   '}, {'comments': "Brendan's apartment was exactly as pictured. Clean, warm and cozy. The beds were comfortable and the neighborhood was filled with wonderful little cafes and restaurants. Very convenient location. We'd stay here again!\r\n"}, {'comments': 'Estuvimos 6 noches en el apartamento de Brendan, el fue muy puntual, siempre dispuesto a apoyar pero respetando privacidad, el apartamento esta muy bien ubicado, dos o tres estaciones del tren muy cercanas, todo de acuerdo a fotos y descripción, muchas gracias Brendan, durante nuestra estancia nos sentimos mas Neoyorkinos que turistas.'}, {'comments': 'The place was clean and conveniently located to lots of good food options nearby.'}, {'comments': 'Brendan was responsive, when i landed early in JFK and reached the apartment before checkin time, Brendan was kind enough to let me leave my luggage with him. The apartment itself is very clean and is in a wonderful location.. this is probably my go to location in Nolita, so look forward to booking again the next time I am in NYC'}, {'comments': 'Brendan was great!  He met me @ midnight to let me in!'}, {'comments': "It went okay when we stayed in Brendan's apartment. Brendan is a very kind host. However, At the first night, we didn't get hot water and it was repaired till next day's afternoon. Brendan said it was rare though. Before I booked the apt, it said the check out time was flexible. But at the night before we checked out, we were told we had to leave by noon. Maybe I didn't get the definition about flexible check out time. I think that's my fault. Just wanna let the other people who want to stay in the place double check the time with the host even before you book it. Anyway, the staying in NYC was fine. Hope you guys can enjoy the city."}, {'comments': 'Brendan was a very responsive and attentive host.  He allowed me and my friends to keep our bags at his place until the apartment was ready and answered texts and questions in a super timely manner.  The apt was very clean and comfortable. Gorgeous neighborhood and felt like I was in good hands.  Would definitely stay with Brendan again.'}, {'comments': 'Brendan was a great host. He was very responsive and everything in the apartment matched exactly. Awesome location close to great restaurants and bars. Would definitely consider it for the next time we visit NYC.'}, {'comments': 'The stay here was excellent! A colleague and I needed a place while on business in the city. Brendan was very accommodating with getting us the keys and working with our schedules. The place was clean and spacious by NYC standards. And the price was phenomenal for a two bedroom! Great location too. Checkout was a breeze.'}, {'comments': 'Nolita is one of the best areas in Manhattan. It is close to everything- walking distance to many special places. But still an original area. The houses are low, the restaurants and bars intimate and the people nice. Brendans place is right in the center of everything and when you are "home", you´ve got everything you need: a nice kitchen/living room and two VERY  separate bedrooms. You can stay here with snoring friends, and don´t be disturbed. It is on the 4th floor and the only thing I missed was a lift. There is a very nice restaurant and a cool bar in the same building. Both worth a visit.\r\n'}, {'comments': "Best location in NYC! Nolita is so trendy and relaxed at the same time in a combined urban coolness :-) We loved our stay in Brendan's apparent were we felt very welcome. Very nice that the two bedrooms are separated by the living room making them both private. The beds a so comfy - real nice after a long flight :-) Btw: The Italian restaurant downstairs (Emporio) is quite good."}, {'comments': "Brendan was an incredible host. I don't think I can fully explain how this past weekend was such a wonderful trip and huge part of that is because of Brendan and this apartment. I have been to NYC a few times before and this was by far the best place I've stayed. He quickly responded to every question we had and truly made us feel welcome. A friend of mine ended up getting to the city earlier than the rest of us and he made sure she had a place to put her bags until we arrived. The apartment became a home away from home and was a perfect location for us for all that we wanted to do. There also were some incredible restaurants and shops in the area if you wanted to go somewhere nearby. I will recommend Brendan's listing to any friend I know coming to NYC."}, {'comments': "We had a great stay at Brendan's place. The location is great and Brendan was very helpful in accommodating our early arrival by keeping our luggage with him. The apartment was clean and as pictured. We did not spend a lot of time in it during the day but we slept very well during the two nights we were there. Definitely a place to come back to."}, {'comments': 'The location for the apartment is perfect. There is a lot of very nice bars and restaurent in the neighbourhood. The condition of the apartment is fine and it was clean. The size of the apartment is perfect for 2 couples. Brendan was very helpful. It was especially nice that the check-in and check-out was flexible.'}, {'comments': 'Great place to stay, Great guy, very helpfull. Everything perfect. '}, {'comments': 'Great time in Brendan flat! The position is very good and the apartment is very nice. Absolutely recommended if you wish to stay in Manhattan!!!'}, {'comments': 'We had a wonderful time and this place was perfect.  Great location and immaculate.  We will definitely try to stay on our next visit to NYC.'}, {'comments': 'We arrived much earlier than we had planned but Brendan graciously let us in to drop our bags while apt. was being prepared for us. The two bedrooms are at opposite ends and both were very clean and comfortable. Great restaurants nearby. This is an amazing location and I would definitely stay again!'}, {'comments': "Brendan a été très accueillant, disponible et flexible. On a pu laisser nos bagages le temps que l'appartement soit prêt.\r\nL'appartement est conforme à la description, très propre et très bien agencé. Sa situation géographique est un gros plus afin de visiter la ville (très proche du quartier financier, chinois et italien), de plus plusieurs stations de métro sont très proches. \r\nMention spéciale au sujet du confort des lits.\r\n\r\nPour résumer : hôte génial, appartement génial, ville géniale.\r\n"}, {'comments': 'Brendan was very nice and helpful. We were able to leave baggage with him hours before check in. Apartment very nice, exactly as described in add. \r\nNeighborhood great, all in walking distance.        '}, {'comments': "Very nice stay in Brendan's appartment in an incredible area of New-York :Near everything and the place to be for entertainment and shopping . \r\nThe appartement is cosy and the two bedrooms very independant and confortable .\r\n"}, {'comments': "The apartment was awesome and suited the 3 of us perfectly. Brendan was friendly & helpful. The location couldn't have been better. We were so central to everywhere. The only downside was the building construction work taking place next door which starts at 7am. Would definitely stay again."}, {'comments': "Easy 'hand over' of keys and a comfortable apartment in a great location. \r\n\r\nThank you Brendan"}, {'comments': "The location was great. Easy to access the subway. Loved the markets of Chinatown, just blocks South and Little Italy.  Place was small for 2 kids in their early 20's and 2 adults. Very small bathroom.  Be prepared to walk 3 flights of stairs. Brendan was available to us if we needed him."}, {'comments': "The location of the apartment is excellent.  It's in the middle of everything or close to subway or walking distance to wherever you need to be in the village.  The location is quiet enough for our babies to sleep and for us to sleep soundly.  \r\n\r\nThe apartment itself is up 3 flights of stairs which are a little run down.  It was clean (kitchen except stove top had grease which was wiped off easily and bathroom) however the floor was unswept and the sheets had stray hairs on them, maybe from laundromat driers.  The apartment consists of two rooms with the kitchen small living and small bathroom with bath inbetween.\r\n\r\nOverall it was a ok stay however cleanliness could be improved.  Thanks!"}, {'comments': 'Brendan was a terrific host! We arrived early so he let us store our bags in his place before the Airbnb was ready. He is great with communicating and was readily available if we had any questions or needed additional supplies (which we did not end up needing). The place itself was very nice. It was in a fantastic location. Very central to everything. I would definitely stay here again!'}, {'comments': 'Great spot to stay so much within walking distance, food, bars, shopping. Subway 5 mins walk and easy to use, maps available and could get to a lot of the well known spots. Once we arrived Brendan very easy to contact & met us with extra supplies, thanks for help with suitcases. Apartment very neat & tidy we didn\'t spend a lot of time "in" plenty of towels and other buts & pieces. Would definitely recommend. Thanks for a great experience.'}, {'comments': 'Excellent spot, lovely host'}, {'comments': 'Staying at brendans Appartement was awesome ! We stayed there for three nights to see New York City and the location and the neighborhood was perfect to get everywhere very quick and reach great dinner places. Also Brendan was very nice and opened. He gave us a great offer to store our luggage at the last day till the afternoon when we departured from New York. Anytime again!'}, {'comments': "Brendan did everything possible to make this a good trip for my family.  We had travel problems (thanks Amtrak!) and were thus four hours late, with Brendan waiting to give us keys.  He made sure we were able to get in easily, which was a relief after a LONG train trip with two kids.  The place itself served perfectly as a home base for some quick touring of the city, in a neighborhood filled with good places to eat.  I'd recommend this place to anyone."}, {'comments': 'Die Kommunikation im Vorfeld und auch bei der Ankunft war perfekt. Er ist sofort gekommen und hat uns die Schlüssel gegeben und uns kurz das Wichtigste erklärt. Wunderbar. Die Wohnung war wie beschrieben: sauber, klein aber sehr schön eingerichtet und für vier Personen vollkommen ausreichend. Vielen Dank für die schöne Zeit in New York!'}, {'comments': "This place was perfect!  My mother, sister, and I were in town for a quick weekend trip.  The place totally suited our needs.  The neighborhood is very quiet, and everyone I interacted with was very nice.  Brendan was a great host and made sure we had everything we needed, very friendly guy who didn't mind getting random text questions:)  Anything you want or need is within a block; Whole Foods is about a 5 minute walk.  I was being adventurous and took the Air Tran and subway and it took me an hour to get there from JFK.  Mom and sister trained to Penn and it was about a 20 minute cab ride from there.  I would totally stay here again!"}, {'comments': "Brendan was so helpful and his apartment was perfect. Wonderful location and Brendan's restaurant recommendations were all very fantastic. Brendan was very flexible and even let us drop our bags at his apartment before check in. I would highly recommend this place to anyone traveling in a small group or just looking for a fun neighborhood to experience while in NY.  Thank you Brendan for a wonderful time !!"}, {'comments': "Joli appartement agréable très bien situé dans un quartier sympathique. Stations de métro à proximité. Salle de bain fonctionnelle. La climatisation d'une des chambres est bruyante. C'est une très bonne expérience."}, {'comments': 'Brendan was on top of the communication with us throughout.  Flat was a bit smaller than what it looked like in the pictures - very narrow but good sized bed rooms.   This place is all about LOCATION.  Nolita is the place to be.  Kitchenette was adequate with basic necessities.   Construction next door was noisy throughout the day during the week, quiet on the weekends.  Looks like construction will continue for several months (large condo project).'}, {'comments': 'Nice area. Good space for 2 couples'}, {'comments': "I would highly recommend Brendan's place because of its location. Subway stations are really close by as well as must-go chinese restaurants. My family and I were able to go visit places in the morning, come back at noon for a short nap, and continue our visit in the afternoon. BTW, the place is also right next to soho for those who like to shop. "}, {'comments': "To guest: If you still hesitate, don't please! I took several weeks to choose the place in Manhattan, finally i was lucky to stay here! Brendan is very good host and he love to help the guest as possible as he can. The apartment is very good which locate in the heart of Manhattan, just 2 minutes to every subway station. I want to emphasis one of advantage of the room, the two BR was separated by a living room which keep the privacy, if you stay with your friends, that is really good. \r\n\r\nTo Brendan, we had amazing time in NYC, appreciate so much for your place! "}, {'comments': 'Great location and great apartment. Central to subway, restaurants and bars. Brendan was there to greet us and give us helpful tips. Two good sized bedrooms with air con. '}, {'comments': 'Brendan was a great host! We got to New York pretty early in the morning and he let us leave our bags in the apartment while it was finishing being cleaned. We really enjoyed where the apartment was located and it was close to a lot of sight-seeing and the subway. The space was a nice size and the beds were very comfortable. I would definitely suggest staying here while in New York!'}, {'comments': 'Great, comfortable place in a vibrant location of Manhattan. As advertised- would highly recommend. '}, {'comments': "Everything went great during our stay here. Arrived to a clean apartment. Brendan was quick to get us inside and give us the tour and let us know how to get in and out of the location. He checked in during out stay to make sure we had everything we needed. \r\n\r\nIt's close to several popular dining spots and also close to other excellent choices you may not be aware of. Also, very quick to subways to get around town.\r\n\r\nBrendan was also helpful in giving us some additional ideas on things to check out while in town. \r\n\r\nOverall, this made my first visit to NYC a very good experience. Thanks!"}, {'comments': 'Brendan was great! very friendly and accommodating.  The apartment was in a great location and surrounded by great restaurants.'}, {'comments': 'Brendan was incredibly responsive and supportive. He catered to all our needs incl. storage of our luggage even many hours after check-out. His place is perfectly located in Nolita very close to a number of cool bars, restaurants and nice shops. Current construction works in the backyard made it a bit noisy but the flat with its two full-blown bed-rooms can generally be highly recommended for a stay in the heart of Manhattan. '}, {'comments': 'Great place and host.'}, {'comments': 'The neighbourhood was awesome. We were in the Center of all of the areas of New York that we wanted to visit. Greenwich village, east village, soho, little Italy, were all within walking distance.  If we wanted to go anywhere else in New York, the subway was very easy to use and stations were only a few blocks away. The apartment was nice and we were able to stay with another married couple comfortably. Great experience!'}, {'comments': 'Brendan var en god og opmærksom vært og bor lige om hjørnet. Han var  hurtig til at svare og gav gode anvisninger/forslag. Det var et fedt område med alt hvad vi havde brug for -  subway, spisesteder og shopping- puha dyrt :-) '}, {'comments': 'Appartement trés bien placé dans le quartier que nous souhaitions. Bon acceuil.'}, {'comments': "Brendan was a wonderful host! Our flight arrived early in the morning and he let us keep our bags at his apt until our rental was ready. He also hauled one of our heaviest bags over while we were out to lunch at a wonderful Italian eatery that he recommended in the neighborhood. The apt was exactly as pictured and was clean and had all the amenities we needed. He was quick to respond to any questions via text. \r\nWe all really enjoyed our stay and would definitely come back to Brendan's place!\r\n"}, {'comments': "L'appartement était parfaitement situé dans un quartier riche en bonnes adresses, petits commerces et restaurants. Plusieurs stations / lignes de métro à proximité vous permettent de vous rendre n'importe où en ville. L'appartement était très propre et meublé avec goût. Les lits confortables. Un seul bémol : dans une des chambres, le chauffage était très bruyant."}, {'comments': 'This place was great! Walking distance to East Village, Lower East Side, Little Italy, Chinatown and more. Would stay here again!'}, {'comments': "Party of 4, stayed for 3 nights. Great apartment, exactly as described. Comfy beds. Lovely location in lower manhattan, just a couple of blocks across from Broadway. 10-15 min subway ride uptown to Times Square, Bryant Park etc from Prince St or Spring St stations. Very small bathroom but wasn't a problem at all. 3 flights of stairs and no elevator which I struggled with being pregnant but I was also aware of this before our stay. Very cosy apartment, we spent very little time here as we were out and about. Would be a squeeze to all watch Tv or eat in the apartment but I doubt many people would be doing that anyway if visiting on a city break. Wasn't an issue for us as we always ate out. I would definitely recommend this apartment. Brendan was really friendly and easy to contact, fast to respond."}, {'comments': 'Brendan was an excellent host who was very quick when answering sms. The place was tidy with two proper bedrooms. The neighborhood was perfect with lots of restaurants and small shops.'}, {'comments': 'Brendan was extremely responsive both before and during our stay. His place is in a perfect location- near the Kool areas like Soho and the Village but also near multiple subway stations to help you get around. I think you get a much more authentic NYC experience staying here than in a hotel. Beds are comfortable-- and just a great place!'}, {'comments': 'Good location, good assistence, little bathroom, \nA little difficult to have dinner for 4 people in the dining room '}, {'comments': "Our train arrived at Penn Station at 8:45 AM.  Our room wasn't going to be free until about 2 PM, which is totally reasonable.  We were worried about what to do with all our suitcases, but Brendan allowed us to store them at his personal residence, a short walk from the rental.  That saved us a lot of money and time, and freed us up to get out and tour the city.  On our departure day, he again let us store our baggage at his place after checkout.  We toured the Met, then went and got dinner in Little Italy, which is just a couple blocks from Brendan's place.  Everything was just super convenient and easy to work with.  Brendan is cheerful, helpful, easy-going.  The room was clean and comfortable, and plenty spacious.  Highly recommended for a great experience in NYC!"}, {'comments': "Brendan was a great host! His apartment was clean and well kept. He was very accommodating and helpful during our stay. His place is close to a subway stop which was very convenient. Overall a great experience and I wouldn't hesitate to stay here again!"}, {'comments': 'Fantastic location in the heart of Nolita, close to Little Italy and Chinatown and so many great restaurants, bars and boutiques. An easy walk to the Spring St subway.\r\nWe thoroughly enjoyed our stay.'}, {'comments': "We stayed for 4 nights at Brendan's place. Everything was nice and ready at our arrival, Brendan was available, quick to answer and very helpful. We loved the charm of the place (the red brick on the wall), the proximity of the subway stations, supermarkets. You can easily do some shopping in Soho or go to Little Italy or Chinatown, it is right around the corner ! The WiFi is good and you can cook your own food if you want. Will do again !"}, {'comments': 'The apartment is fantastic, everything is exactly as shown in the pictures. The neighbourhood has many great places to eat and metro stops are close by (3 min walk). Brendan is a wonderful host, he is always available and very personable. I would happily stay here again during my next visit to New York!'}, {'comments': 'The apartment was just what we needed.  Brendan was helpful in answering our questions.  The description of the apartment accurate. It was clean  Close to subways for easy transportation .  We would definitely stay here again.'}, {'comments': "Absolutely loved our stay at Brendan's place in New York. Brendan was friendly and greeted us as soon as we arrived and gave us a brief tour with a guide to the area. \n\nThe apartment itself was very clean and well furnished. The two bedrooms, kitchen and bathroom had everything you would need and our stay was extremely comfortable. \n\nThe best part was the location, with loads of shops and places to eat within walking distance. Would definitely stay here again the next time I visit New York. "}, {'comments': "We loved the location of Brendan's place and I'd be happy to stay there during another trip. The photos give a very accurate representation of the apartment. It is up 3 flights of narrow stairs in sort of dirty hallways but it wasn't a problem at all. The apartment is upstairs above a restaurant that looked nice and did a brisk business although we didn't end up eating there. The neighborhood was great - it is a residential street with cute boutiques and eateries. We walked to STOMP (had great Risotto dinner beforehand) and to 911 Memorials and to the Brooklyn Bridge and NYU - all within 1/2 hour walk. Little Italy and Chinatown are within a few blocks. Whole Foods is 3 blocks away and Dean & Deluca the opposite direction and a CVS is a block away so food and incidentals are easily taken care of. There was construction next door so that noise was present from about 8 a.m. onward but not a problem for us. Several metro lines are available within about 3-5 blocks - getting home after seeing Broadway shows was easy. Yelp gives 4.5 stars to many of the local eateries so lots of choice. We had a car and had reserved a spot at a garage on-line beforehand. Access was very easy from coming in via Holland Tunnel. \n\nWe stayed in the winter and the apartment has steam heating (which seems typical for the area) so apartment was quite warm - we had to ditch our sweaters when in the apartment. The place is very narrow and the bathroom was tiny. We were a family of 4 with 2 big teen boys and apartment worked fine for us but we didn't try to eat anything other than breakfast or snacks in the apartment - there are only 2 stools in the kitchen. We wanted to use our AppleTV but the TV is an older model without HDMI. It is large and there is cable. We appreciated that there was a closet with plenty of hangers in each bedroom as well as plenty of drawer space so we could stash our clothes away and not have to live out of a suitcase. The kitchen was well stocked with miscellaneous spices, coffee, tea and such. \n\nBrendan was very responsive to communications and happy to accommodate us with storing our bags when we arrived early before the apartment had been cleaned. We didn't need any help during out stay but definitely felt that Brendan would have been there to help us out if we needed recommendations etc. Overall we would highly recommend this apartment."}, {'comments': 'Great place, even better location. Lots is great places to eat and drink nearby. Easy walk to Chinatown, Little Italy and a Whole Foods Market right down the street. '}, {'comments': 'It was nice staying here! Thank you, we had great time exploring New York City.'}, {'comments': 'Perfect place to explore Manhattan and great communication with the host.'}, {'comments': 'Brendan was a great host. His home was clean and in a great location. I would definitely recommend staying here.'}, {'comments': 'Location was perfect  close to great restaurants and shopping \nFriendly people all around. '}, {'comments': 'Absolutely perfect location for a fun vacation!'}, {'comments': 'Great spot!'}, {'comments': "Appart sympa bien placé \nSeul bémol le bruit du chauffage et la chaleur dans l'appartement (nécessité d'ouvrir les fenêtres pour dormir)"}, {'comments': "Really brilliantly located appartment - for bars, restaurants and shopping! Small apartment but perfect for a city break or work. Do note you have to climb three flights of quite steep stairs! It's a bit noisy - but that's because it's in a fun, bustling neighbourhood. Brendan was a great host - even coming round at 11pm to bring electric heaters when the heating broke due to works next door. "}, {'comments': "Brendan's place is in the perfect location, in addition to being very clean and comfortable. My friends and I greatly appreciated the flexibility with check in and check out times. I would highly recommend staying here, and would love to return in the future. "}, {'comments': "Great apartment, great location. We'll definitely be back. "}, {'comments': "Brendan is nice. Always available and with a quick response eventhough he was out of the city. Communication was fluid and he is really understanding. \nWe went in a family trip for five days. With two teens, no babies.\nThe apartment is placed in a nice and trendy neighborhood with many restaurants and small lovely shops around. Subway is really close to the apartment. We didn't took any taxi because we didn't need it. \nThe weather was really cold at those days at NY but  Brendan's apartment has a very good heating. The street is quite by night. We slept very well. At the date we were there, was a construction at the corner but they started to work around 8am, at that time we were already awake to see the city. Beds are really comfortable and bedrooms are not connected, are in the oposite side of the apartment, good point. Kitchen is practical and sitting room has a big size TV, and the sofa is comfortable, from my point of view, a bit small for 4 adults.\nBuilding has no elevator. For us it wasn't a problem. The stairs of the portal and the common areas need a bit cleaning. \nTo resume, Brendan is fully trustworthy. The most important point to me. The apartment is really well placed and connected, and all of this compensate the very small issues it has.\n"}, {'comments': 'Perfect location. Great apartment.'}, {'comments': 'Great location and well appointed!'}, {'comments': 'Brendan may not want to hear this, but this is a great apartment for families.  It\'s a quick walk to Little Italy for gelato and Chinatown for stuff we don\'t need. The kids loved both. Great restaurants nearby where the staff were lovely to us even though Yelp proclaimed them to not be "kid friendly" (we ate early). \n\nTwo large comfortable bedrooms/beds separated by the kitchen, bath, and living room.  The apartment and rooms were clutter free, so there were lots of places for my kids to put (and hide their things).  A bathtub for the kids was a huge plus. Clean and plenty of room. Brendan is responsive and had great restaurant recs.  It\'s a walk-up but my kids were champs about it. '}, {'comments': 'Brendan had wonderful communication and the check-in and check-out process was very smooth. Everything was perfect and the location was very near where I needed to be.'}, {'comments': "Brendan's place is in a great location for a visit to NYC. He was easy to coordinate with, and the apartment was perfect for our needs."}, {'comments': "The apartment is exactly as pictured. Enough storage for clothes so you don't need to live out of your suitcase. Three of us stayed in the apartment for a week and it was very comfortable and there was everything we could need. Some great restaurants within walking distance and a restaurant just downstairs which had nice food and great service or you could just have a drink. SoHo, Little Italy, Chinatown all within walking distance. Some great shopping too. Brendan was great with communication and responded almost immediately each time we needed to contact him. We also arrived late at night (1.30am to be exact) and Brendan made it easy for us to check-in. We had a great stay and I don't hesitate in recommending Brendan's place."}, {'comments': 'It was good to stay there.'}, {'comments': "Be aware of the bed bugs. The place is in great location and spacious, but the bed wasn't clean and the hygiene was also quite bad."}, {'comments': "Brendan's place is so nice! It couldn't have been better for 4 of us ladies traveling to NY for classes at the Deva Academy which was a few blocks away! Nolita is the best neighborhood filled with tons of great food, bars, boutiques and easy to get anywhere. I would definitely recommend this home!"}, {'comments': 'Great apartment for two couples. Good location and neighbourhood. I recommend.'}, {'comments': 'Highly responsive host. Perfect location if you want to be in the bustle of Soho (which we did). Near subways and the New Museum, too. It is up three flights of stairs, which was not a problem for us but might be a factor for some people. We would choose to stay here again.'}, {'comments': 'Completely met expectations.  Recommend the apartment.'}, {'comments': "Amazing location! Though the place is in the heart of Soho, the building is quiet and there's not too much street noise. Check in was a breeze, Brendan communicates super fast and accommodated our early arrival."}, {'comments': 'Great place to be in NY and to discover the city. It is very easy to start the trips around NY by tube or just walk around for shopping, having lunch or an drink. We loved it! We spend 4 days with two adults and two teenager at Brendans place. Everything worked out fine. Brendan is very kind and helpful. Thank you Brendan!  We would come again:-))'}, {'comments': "Brendan was very great with communicating and he was available to answer all our questions.  \nThe place is exactly as described.  If you are a light sleeper I would suggest the back room since you can hear all the street noise from the front bedroom.  The apartment had everything we needed and was in a great location.  \nI would definitely stay at Brendan's place again.  "}, {'comments': 'Hands down, Brendan was the best host by far. If you are lucky enough to score his place, you will be inundated with options for food, drinks, dessert, and have the ultimate luxury in accessing the subway because of its fantastic location. He was an absolute pleasure to deal with and was very accessible for anything we needed. He also put us in touch with a friend who was a concierge so we could ask any questions about what to see and do. The Airbnb made our trip one of the best ever!'}, {'comments': 'Brendan was very accommodating, we were able to have an early check in and a late check out. \nApartment is very central and in an excellent location, beside nice restaurants and shops. Apartment is spacious for NYC, with 2 good sized bedrooms and a nice living area with a full kitchen. We were a family of 4 and stayed for 6 nights and would recommend this apartment'}, {'comments': "Location location location. If you want to know what it feels like living downtown, stay here. Nolita is close to everything and a subway away from everything. We barely used the apartment - just to rest and sleep. A/c units in the bedrooms worked well. \n\nOur favorite neighborhood eateries - officina Latina, cafe habana, the coffee place across the street (forgetting the name), the bar downstairs (not emporio, the other tiny one). A tiny bit more of a walk - Balthazar, Bens famous pizza for a quick slice, Lupa, and Rauols.  \n\nDidn't meet Brendan, our host, yet he ensured we received the key and had what we needed. Almost immediately would respond to our messages, which was really nice. "}, {'comments': "Brendan's space is exactly as pictured. In a great neighbourhood with lots to see and do."}, {'comments': 'Great'}, {'comments': "Brendan's apartment si exactly as shown in the pictures.\nThe key delivery was seamless, without any inconvenience.\nThe location is perfect, the neighborhood is very trendy and walking- Distance to Soho, Village, Greenwich.\nBrendon was very accomodating and the communication with him was easy and fluid.\nI recommend Brandan' apartment."}, {'comments': 'I loved the place and location. Would stay here again.'}, {'comments': "I had a great stay at what I would consider the perfect location and in the best place I needed to stay for my first visit to New York City. \n\nI rented Brendan's place for five days and was more than satisfied. Bathroom was clean, Kitchen had all the necessary appliances needed for cooking, and the place was in a great location for transportation and dinning out.\n\nTo give some perspective on size: We had one person in each of the two bed rooms, one on an air mattress and shared one bathroom but still felt like everyone had enough space and privacy to enjoy our stay when we needed to sleep or eat.\n\nBrendan was a great host. He maintained a lot of clear, respectful and responsive communication for my entire stay. \n\nI would absolutely recommend his place to others and I will certainly consider staying here again if I find myself back in New York City.\n\nThanks again Brendan. "}, {'comments': 'Loved the place, the low key atmosphere the location was convenient to everything and parking was awesome. Brendan was very helpful as well as a great communicator through out.'}, {'comments': 'The location was great'}, {'comments': 'Great place, 10/10. Great location. Safe neighbourhood, great places that eat and easy transport. Would recommend without hesitation. Thanks.'}, {'comments': 'Best location in town'}, {'comments': "We had a great stay in Nolita at Brendan's apartment. It is in such an excellent location. Plenty of towels, blankets and the A/C was a nice addition. May not be the best for those of you who aren't a fan on climbing steps to the third floor. Not a problem for us, just an FYI! Brendan was great to communicate with and would definitely recommend."}, {'comments': "This is my second stay at Brendon's place- I love the central location and the great vibe of the Nolita- Soho area. Lots of interesting bars and restaurants close by. Would definitely recommend."}, {'comments': "Cet appartement est parfaitement situé, à distance de marche de presque tout! C'était propre et fonctionnel. Il est situé au 3e étage toutefois et il n'y a pas d'ascenseur donc pas idéal pour les gens moins en forme, ce qui n'était toutefois pas notre cas, donc ce ne fut pas un problème pour nous. Brendan avait laissé des indications claires, et était disponible au besoin. Le restaurant Emporio situé tout juste en bas de l'appartement était une très belle découverte...absolument délicieux!! Pour le stationnement, il y a quelques stationnements publics aux alentours, dont certains qu'on peut même réserver et payer à l'avance. Laissez votre voiture bien stationnée durant votre séjour, et privilégiez la marche, le métro ou le taxi, car la circulation à NY est difficile en voiture!\nBref, je recommande cet appartement sans hésiter, surtout que les logements à deux chambres sont plutôt rares (ou très chers)... \nMerci Brendan!"}, {'comments': 'Great location! It has some noise in r/w building right next to it is under construction. Otherwise, size/age of apartment as expected for NY'}, {'comments': 'Brendan’s place is a real NYC experience and he was so great to work with.  Being in Little Italy was a great way to spend our time with deli’s, restaurants and shops so close.  We would recommend it to all.'}, {'comments': "We loved staying at Brendan's place and will definitely choose to stay here again next time we're in NYC! The house is perfectly situated in Nolita/SoHo, among fantastic restaurants and shopping, and close to subway stations. The apartment is small, but beautifully kept - everything was clean, the kitchen and bathroom were stocked, beds were comfortable, and the TV was an added bonus. Just beware the apartment a walk-up and three stories up, so you'll have to carry any luggage up and down stairs. We enjoyed our stay immensely and definitely recommend it for your next trip!"}, {'comments': "Brendan's apartment is great! Perfect location and super clean. And our stay was made 1000x better because Brendan was kind enough to accommodate our weird check-in and check-out logistics."}, {'comments': 'Nous avons passé un agréable séjour chez Brendan'}, {'comments': 'Everything you need in this space efficient New York apartment. Great neighbourhood and much less street traffic than in many other parts of Manhattan. Brendan always answered our inquiries quickly and politely. A reliable host that only wants the best for his guests.'}, {'comments': 'We had a great time in NYC which was aided by Brendan’s centrally located apartment. Flexible check-in, good communication, and no surprises. Recommended.'}, {'comments': "Can't ask for a better location. This is a city apartment so if you are a light sleeper choose the bedroom on the right. Brendan responded quickly and accommodated our check-in times! Would definitely stay again!"}, {'comments': 'Accurate description. 10/10 location. Hip neighborhood. Well equipped apt. Spacious beds. Tiny bathroom tho + noisy neighboors above. Loud noises from streets + restaurant backyards - no problem for us as we were all sleeping tight. Can get cold during fall/winter.\n\nCouldn‘t be more happy with the perfect communication and location of the apt!'}, {'comments': 'Great place in a great location, quiet neighborhood with everything in walking distance, it was perfect for the 4 of us who stayed there.  Brendan was very quick in his responses back to us from all of our questions!'}, {'comments': 'Great place to stay in manhattan, area is fantastic so you can explore on foot and there are loads of restaurants nearby. Slightly unusual heating system that can be a little noisy but you get used to it - and the apartment is up three flights of stairs so you’ve got to carry your suitcases up! Brendan is really easily contactable and very helpful. We had a great stay, thanks Brendan!'}, {'comments': 'Great location! Nice apartment and good attention from the landlord. Only cleaningness and tidiness could be better. It’s fine though I think sheets should be ironed and have no stains of bleach...'}, {'comments': 'Exactly as advertised.  Great location in Nolita.  Host is quick to respond.  Good experience.'}, {'comments': 'Nice big apartment with perfect location. Comfortable beds and tidy kitchen and bathroom. Easy communication with host. Warm despite freezing temperatures outside.'}, {'comments': "Brendan was a terrific host.  The apartment is centrally located and there are tons of great restaurants and shopping nearby.  Bedrooms at opposite ends of the apartment are great for privacy.  The building is quiet, I got great sleep while we were there.  I am glad I stayed at Brendan's place, it was everything I expected."}, {'comments': "Brendan's place is great - well stocked with what you need (shampoo, bandaides, etc...), perfect location, clean -and above all else if you there's something you need Brendan is on top of it, he's a great guy :)"}, {'comments': 'Great Apartment, cozy and very warm.Very very clean and in a great location near to restaurants, bars and near to mid town manhattan. Brendan was very kind and help us a lot with our check out. Only issue if you go winter there is a little bit annoying noise from the radiators but the apartment was very very hot for the cold nights with -8C degrees. For sure I will choose this apartment next time to NY.'}, {'comments': 'Kurz zu der Reise Gruppe - eine Frau, zwei Männer\nDie Wohnung war super. Die Aufteilung, mit den beiden Schlafzimmern auf der jeweils entgegen gelegenen Seite des Wohn-/Gemeinschaftsraums war für unser Gruppe perfekt. Genügend Privatsphäre.\nDas Bad war gut ausgestattet.\nDie Küche hatte alles was man braucht (keine Spülmaschine). Bisschen mehr Besteck wäre gut gewesen hat aber vollkommen gereicht.\nAls Unterkunft, für uns als verwöhnte Deutsche, sehr zufriedenstellend.\n\nDer größte Pluspunkt allerdings war die Lage. Ein kleiner Lebensmittelladen die Straße runter (aber nicht günstig – an der 33rd Straße ist ein Target wo man alles nötige bekommt) und die U-Bahn Stationen Spring Street, Lafayette oder Bowery Station.\nSpring und Bowery waren unsere ansicht nach die wichtigsten. Von Spring Street aus mit der Linie 6 entweder nach Norden zur 33rd Street (nahe Empire State Building), 42nd (Grend Central), 59th (Stück östlich vom Central Park) oder mit der Linie 4 nach Süden Fulton Street raus und man ist nahe World Trade Center.\nBowery perfekt für die An- und Abreise. Die Linie J und Z verbinden diese mit der Airtrain (Linie Rot) mit dem Flughafen JFK (Fahrzeit insgesamt rund 1:30 Stunde). Ihr braucht eine Metro Card (7 Tage 33 USD und ein Ticket für die Airtrain 5 USD) die ihr dort am Automaten lösen könnt. Eine Karte kann für beides genutzt werden.\n\nAls Alternative zum Hotel definitiv empfehlenswert. Als Gastgeber, war Brandan ebenfalls sehr zuvorkommend.\n\n-----\n\nBriefly to the travel group - one woman, two men\nThe apartment was great. The layout, with the two bedrooms on the opposite side of the living room/common room, was perfect for our group. Enough privacy.\nThe bathroom was well equipped.\nThe kitchen had everything you need (no dishwasher). A little more cutlery would have been good but was quite all right.\nAs accommodation, for us as spoiled Germans, very satisfactory.\n\nThe biggest advantage, however, was the location. A small grocery store down the street (but not cheap - at 33rd Street is a Target where you can get everything you need) and the subway stations Spring Street, Lafayette or Bowery Station.\nSpring and Bowery were the most important ones from our point of view. From Spring Street, take Line 6 either north to 33rd Street (near Empire State Building), 42nd (Grend Central), 59th (east of Central Park) or Line 4 south to Fulton Street and you are close to World Trade Center.\nBowery perfect for arrival and departure. The J and Z lines connect them with the Airtrain (line red) and the JFK airport (travel time about 1:30 hours). You need a Metro Card (7 days 33 USD and a ticket for the Airtrain 5 USD) which you can buy there at the vending machine. A card can be used for both.\n\nDefinitely recommended as an alternative to the hotel. As a host, Brandan was also very thoughtful.\n\nTranslated with (Website hidden by Airbnb)'}, {'comments': 'I was here with my boyfriend, my sister and her husband. It is perfect for two couples. This part of Manhattan is great and we felt safe all the time. The apartment was clean and well equipped. Few subway stations are just few minutes walking from the apartment. The location is perfect! Everything is so close with subway and even by walking distance. Brendan is great host. He was very helpful and he approved late check out beacuse of our evening flight. We are very grateful and we definitely recommend this place!'}, {'comments': 'Awesome place, great host, cute apartment, and lovely neighborhood!'}, {'comments': 'Great location. Very nice Apartment. Absolutely more then we had expected for the price. Nice neighborhood. Everything you need is in walking distance (Whole Foods, CVS, lot‘s of cool Bars & Restaurants). \nBrendan was a great Host! Fast answers, great tips for things to see and do in the area. We had some problems with our flights, both on arrival and departure and Brendan was a great help and very flexible with the check-in and check-out.\n\nWe  highly recommend his place and would absolutely  stay again at Brendans Apartment'}, {'comments': 'Un excellent accueil ! Très très réactif et très arrangeant pour l’heure du Check in et Check lit! \nJe vois elle recommande vivement ! \nBrendan est une personne au top ! \nA faire et refaire ! Réservez ! n’hésitez plus !'}, {'comments': 'It was such an amazing stay!!!'}, {'comments': 'The flat is very well equipped and the location is perfect (in a nice neighborhood with everything you need in walking distance).\nJust the communication could have been faster, but I guess time zone differences can explain some of it.'}, {'comments': 'What an amazing location. Right in the heart of restaurants, bars, shopping and so close the subway. The place was three flights up, which was fine, and it was relatively spacious and very clean.  Bathroom was tight, but the bedrooms were plenty big, and both had windows that could open! We had a great time, would definitely return.'}, {'comments': 'Great place!  Very close to subways so easy to go anywhere. Great little coffee shop on the corner. Brendan is quick to answer and very helpful. Highly recommend!!'}, {'comments': "We had an excellent stay at Brendan's place. The apartment looks exactly as portrayed in the pictures. Its key strength is its location right in the middle of Nolita which is close to Soho, The Village, Little Italy and we even walked uptown!\nYou need to take into account that the apartment is on the 4th floor with no elevator. Also, we came to eat out so had no problem (Try the Italian which is right in the same building! by the entrance), if more than two want to eat  in the apartment - it could become a challenge as there is no space for that. As I said, when you visit NYC and you have a café two steps away and lots of restaurants all around, that should not be the issue. \nBrendan is an excellent communicator in the sense that he reacts immediately to anything you asked (before and during our stay) and doesn't nag at all!\nThanks for a great time in NYC!"}, {'comments': "Excellent location. Walking distance to Tribeca FF venues and a plethora of food. Cozy and comfy apartment. Couldn't have asked for better for our business trip."}, {'comments': "Appartement sympa et confortable, dans un quartier très intéressant du point de vue de la localisation comme des nombreux commerces qu'on peut y trouver. Station de métro proche. Brendan a été très réactif et arrangeant. Bref, c'était top !"}, {'comments': "Brendan's place was clean, cozy, and in a fantastic location. A+"}, {'comments': 'Appartement sympa et confortable dans un quartier top. Plusieurs lignes de métro à proximité et très bonne communication avec Brendan.  Nous recommandons et nous reviendrions avec plaisir!'}, {'comments': 'Brendan est un hôte très accueillant et disponible pour toutes questions . Nous avons adoré le quartier avec ses petites boutiques et ses délicieux restaurants et son métro à proximité . \nL’appartement était très propre et la literie de super qualité , nous avons adoré séjourné dans l’appartement typique New yorkais de Brendan avec nos amis !'}, {'comments': 'Brendans place was exactly what we needed and in the perfect spot for a great time in Nolita. Communication was great!'}, {'comments': '100 points. We would come back. Thank you Brendan.'}, {'comments': 'Very Nice. Stairs not a nuisance. Very nice shops close by. CVS close walk. Felt safe the whole time. Would definitely stay here again.'}, {'comments': 'We loved your flat Brendan - it was so nice to come back to after a busy day out. The location is superb and we couldn’t recommend it highly enough. \nWould definitely come back if ever lucky enough to visit New York again.'}, {'comments': "Fantastic apartment in a great neighbourhood. Checkin and checkout were easy and Brendan's communication was excellent. Apartment has loads of room and was very pleasant to stay in. Location couldn't have been better - Nolita is ideal for getting the subway to pretty much anywhere, and very walkable to lots of Manhattan. We enjoyed lots of Brendan's restaurant tips as well. Would definitely stay here again!"}, {'comments': "A great apartment in a great location. It is compact but felt spacious for 3 people, I'm sure it would for 4 too. Very easy to pick up the keys. Brendan checked in to see if everything was ok, which was nice. He also left milk etc in the fridge for us on arrival. The air con worked really well (much needed in July!) but was a bit noisy at times. Apart from that, a great stay."}, {'comments': 'Great place in a great location.'}, {'comments': "Brendan place is exactly as you can see it in the picture. It's nice, cosy and it look like a classic NY apartment.  It makes you feel living not as a tourist in NY.\n\nWe found all the ncecessary, to make coffee or cook something.\n\nThe place was clean and it's situated in a perfect location. Between Soho and Nolita. Just 10 minutes walking to the supermarket (Whole Food market) and very closed to different subway. \n\nI reccomend Brendan's place!\n\nIf I have to recriminate something: just the noice of the air conditioning. But if you are tired after a long walk around NY it won't bother you! \n "}, {'comments': 'Perfect location to visit NY. Local Area very friendly with lot of restaurant and bar.'}, {'comments': 'Brendan is a great host! Really interested in your comfort and does his best. Location is just perfect - everything you need is so close and is very comfortable for using public transportation. The place also is quiet and safe - exactly what you need after a busy day.'}, {'comments': 'Excelente ubicacion, cómodo, práctico y una excelente relacion precio-calidad-ubicacion.\nMuy recomendable si te gusta vivir en esta zona de NY. Volveremos!'}, {'comments': "Location location location. I doubt there is a better area to stay in Manhatten. Close to everything we walked everywhere and didnt use any public transport. food and drink options right outside your door are numerous and all of great quality. The Fiat cafe serves up great italian food and the Thai next door was fantastic. Parisi bakery over the road has probably the best sandwiches ive ever eaten, you have to try 'The Dennis', amazing! Great coffee for Gimme Coffee directly opposite the apartment. \nGreat to see hardly any chains mostly all independants both shops and eateries, SOHO is just round the corner for upscale shopping and all the usual suspects are there. \n\nThe apartment is a great size and very clean and functional, there was only 2 of us but 4 could stay comfortably. Everything you need for your stay is in the apartment. We really enjoyed our stay and wouldnt hesitate to stay again on future trips."}, {'comments': 'Nice location, close to beautiful Soho'}, {'comments': "Brendan's place is the perfect location in Soho! You are at the intersection of several subway lines - everything is so easy to get to from there! Would definitely stay again."}, {'comments': 'the location its awesome!!!'}, {'comments': 'Apartment is in an excellent location. Very stylish area with lots of bars and restaurants and quick access to the subway. We had a friend visit who lives in NY and she was stunned at how big the apartment was. I wouldn’t hesitate to stay here again.'}, {'comments': 'Great location. Everything at your feet. The Emporio Restaurant downstairs has the best Italian food we have ever eaten!\n\nHowever the property didn’t meet our expectations, not even down to the basic standards.'}, {'comments': 'Perfect location for exploring lower Manhattan. Centrally located and a great restaurant just downstairs. The apartment itself was perfect for our family of 4 (we have a 1 and a 4 year old and everyone slept well). The walk up isn’t hard, but the stairs are a bit steeper than usual.'}, {'comments': "PRIME location. Such a fun area, tons of restaurants, one of the bedrooms doesn't face the street so it's pretty quiet. I'd stay here again."}, {'comments': "Brendan's place was the perfect solution for us! I was traveling with my family and we had a great stay. \nThe two rooms are spacious and the house is perfect for 4 people. The bathroom is small but if you know NY its just normal :) \nThe house its just like in the photos,  it's a warm place and very functional. \nThe location is just PERFECT to explore the city. I know NY pretty well and really wanted to stay in this area, You can walk to a lot of great places and have different metro lines close by to move all around. Lots of good restaurants, bars and shops. Best choice!\nBrendan is always reachable and ready to help. The house has everything you need and the kitchen is perfect for good breakfast to start your day.\nI would definitely stay here again next time and suggest to others!"}, {'comments': 'Nice apartment, best location!!! Very close to numerous subway stations / lines\nFor sure deserves a second stay!!!\nThe host was very kind and reachable by messages\nVery nice Check-in / checkout system\nThis apartment is a no brainer!!'}, {'comments': 'perfectly located and charming 2 bedrooms flat! perfect for a family up to 2 children and top for 2 couples or friends. All kind of facilities, transports, shops and of course bar and restaurants down the building... Brendan is also very reactive if needed...'}, {'comments': 'Great location.'}, {'comments': 'Close to China town. We can get grocery and make dinner. Awesome'}, {'comments': 'I’m a local resident who needed a place for my family and myself to stay while our place was having work done. His space (and its location) were very good and matched the depiction. Brendan was a very helpful and accommodating host. Thank you.'}, {'comments': 'Brendan’s apartment is comfy and most importantly, he is responsive and the apartment is in a GREAT location.'}, {'comments': "We enjoyed to stay at Brendan's place. The location is amazing and the apartment is very cute!"}, {'comments': 'This place is cozy, great location—groceries, whole food market are close, easy to go everywhere and many good restaurants near by. \nWe spent almost a month and nothing was inconvinient, very quiet neighborhood but also middle of the soho. I just liked this place so much it’s like home home :)'}], 'score': 0.7062661051750183}
{'name': 'Walk to beach - Cottage close to Waikiki', 'neighborhood_overview': "What I love about this neighborhood is that is pretty melow and quiet, but if you walk about six blocks you find all the action in waikiki and of course I love the fact that is so close to the ocean and the beautiful Kapiolani Park and you can see people exercising, kids playing in the park, etc, it's really amazing,", 'property_type': 'House', 'bedrooms': 3, 'address': {'street': 'Honolulu, HI, United States', 'suburb': 'Diamond Head/Kapahulu/St. Louis Heights', 'government_area': 'Primary Urban Center', 'market': 'Oahu', 'country': 'United States', 'country_code': 'US', 'location': {'type': 'Point', 'coordinates': [-157.81261, 21.27219], 'is_location_exact': False}}, 'reviews': [{'comments': "I went to Oahu on a girls trip with 8 of my friends for my birthday. We wanted to find a place that was close enough to Waikiki to party in the bars, but easy access to the highways to explore the island and not have to pay for hotel parking overnight. This place met all of our wishes. There is plenty of street parking and the neighborhood feels safe enough. It's not the fanciest neighborhood, but we were very comfortable and felt like locals. The house was very clean and decorated well. The beds were comfortable, but more on the firm side, FYI. The kitchen had all the necessary tools and every appliance worked well. The bathroom was clean and the shower had strong water pressure. There is a washer and dryer that works well, but we only used it once since Marylu had left plenty of linens and towels for us. There is a large Safeway grocery store about a mile away, and a liquor store and gas station just a couple blocks down the street.\r\n\r\nMarylu was very quick to respond to my emails and was very accommodating even though we didn't need anything else or have any complaints.  \r\n\r\nWe had an amazing time and a big reason was this cottage. If I ever visit Honolulu again, I would definitely stay here again!"}, {'comments': "Great house! It's about a 20-25 min walk to Waikiki Beach. Very well stocked with dishes, washer & dryer, etc. Lots of places to sleep and extra sofas. We fit 8 people in here comfortably with shared beds. Definitely recommended. "}, {'comments': 'Marylu and her cottage were fantastic. Exactly what we needed for our trip. Never using airbnd before she was great.  Quick responses, and helpful.  The place was cute and a 15 min walk to the beach, not much further to downtown Waikiki.  All the food places around it were recommended to us by locals.  Nice neighborhood also.'}, {'comments': 'I never met Marilu, but she was very kind and nice and very service minded via mail and text messages. \nThe house was great for us, five people. There is just three bedrooms so if your are ten people it would be tight. But the washing machine and the kitchen was perfect and the small garden. \n. The cleaning was ok, but some dust here and there.  \nThe neighbour hood is so good, eat at Diamonnd head grill and est an acai bowl at Bogarts café for vreakfast. Its so good! '}, {'comments': 'Absolutely perfect! Very helpful landlady, everything was very easy and we loved staying here. For a group of 5 of us there was more than enough space, and there were still spare beds! Great location too. Thank you so much for making this place so hospitable, definitely recommend it : )'}, {'comments': "Overall we had a very good experience. The cottage is your typical island style design and layout. It was clean, had all of the necessities and easy to find street parking. \r\n\r\nLocation is great, close to Waikiki, diamond head, grocery store and shops. However, Campbell Avenue is a busy street and road noise can be pretty loud. Buses start early in the morning. The third bedroom is small compared to the other two however, you are only going to use it to sleep, you're in Hawaii after all. \r\n\r\nWe had 3 couples in the place and never felt cramped. The kitchen came in handy as did the BBQ. All of us agreed we would certainly stay here again and Marylu was great to work with. She was prompt with responding to inquiries. "}, {'comments': 'The cottage is lovely. It is a great place for a family or a group of friends. We were delighted to find all kind of treats in the kitchen and all needed for cooking. The sofas are comfortable and the hard wood floors beautiful. The walk to the beach is right past the zoo!'}, {'comments': "The house was perfect!  We fit a group of seven comfortably when we were in town for a friend's wedding.  The well-supplied kitchen meant we could save money by preparing several meals at the house.  But the house is also close to the beach (~20 min. walk) and several good places to eat, including the delicious Side Street Inn.  \r\n\r\nI loved reading and barbecuing in the yard.  There were plenty of towels and beach supplies for everyone.  Besides the bathroom being a bit busy with seven people, it was very clean and the shower pressure and temperature level were great.  The welcome package was a nice touch.  \r\n\r\nAs others have mentioned, the only issue we had was with noise.  There's not much sound insulation between the house and the street or the neighboring houses.  I would suggest bringing earplugs if you're a light sleeper.  Also, the neighbors stopped by one night to ask that we keep the conversation down after 10 so that's good to keep in mind in advance.  \r\n\r\nAlso, a lot of the outlets are two-prong.  It could be useful to bring a 3-prong to 2-prong adapter.  \r\n\r\nWe'd all definitely stay again - thanks so much!  \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n"}, {'comments': 'The house was better than expected! Very relaxful place, with a short walk to the main strip. Wish we could have stayed there longer.'}, {'comments': 'Great beach house and close to everything! Marylu was responsive during the whole booking process and we would absolutely book with her again. House was clean and we had a great time!'}, {'comments': "My group and I were very please to stayed at Marylu's place. It honestly feels like home and Marylu makes you feel secure by responding quickly to your messages. Highly recommend this place to anybody planning on staying in waikiki."}, {'comments': 'The house was amazing!  Clean, spacious, and comfortable.  Marylu was very accommodating and flexible.  The yard was very nice to hang out in, and the location was excellent, much better than Waikiki.  Beautiful view of Diamond Head.  Beach supplies were even provided.  We had a large group and we all fit in comfortably, plenty of bedding, blankets and pillows.  Would highly recommend!'}, {'comments': "Marylu had a great place that I would definitely recommend. Check in and check out were smooth and no hassle. Marylu was a responsive host and moved our check in time up to accomodate our arrival time. The house is in a good location with the famous Ono's right down the street and Waikiki easily within reach."}, {'comments': 'Marylu is kind and her response is also very quick. She is flexible for various requests. About this listing, the contents of many feedbacks are right. A positive is access to Waikiki, Diamond head, Kahala, and H1 is very nice. The cost performance is also good. A negative is road noise, but  this house is recommended for a lengthier stay and for who is not so nervous. \r\n'}, {'comments': "The house was perfect for everything we needed. Close enough to walk to the beach and Waikiki, but far enough away to avoid all the hustle & bustle of the busy tourist area. Leonard's Malasadas, Zippy's, and Safeway are all in the neighborhood. The house is relatively close to the neighbors, and your windows will be open because of the heat so you have to be conscious to not be too loud at night. We had a little trouble getting a hold of Marylu at first, but that was due to her being out of the country. She was still able to connect with us to make sure we had the necessary check-in information. Overall, my friends and I had a great stay and I can't wait to come back!"}, {'comments': "We had an absolutely great stay at Marylu's cottage. It was so 'old Hawaii'...just what we love. The place is well-equipped with tons of towels, comfy beds and a fully-stocked kitchen...perfect for the omelets I made my family every morning. The street traffic can be a little loud, but no worries since the place is so comfortable. Oh, and the mango tree outside provided the perfect sweet treat! All in all, a wonderful stay. Thanks!"}, {'comments': "Host:\r\nMarylu made this trip easy through her ease of communication leading to the trip and during. If I had any questions Marylu would respond quickly. She also made the check in and check out process easy.\r\nRental:\r\nThe location of the house is ideal for a visit to Honolulu. It is literally 8-10 mins away from everything you need; Waikiki beach, restaurants, Safeway, Starbucks and bars. We would take a cab to most of these places and the fare was always less than $10. the house has many beds. I think it can fit up to a group of 10 people. There is no A/C but the windows and ceiling fans through out made the house cooler. Marylu also provided extra towels and bed sheets which were very helpful. We were unable to get the washer machine to work and had to go to the laundry mat near by. Instructions on the machine would have helped. Also there is no microwave only a stove, coffee maker, fridge and dishwasher. A microwave would have definitely been used and appreciated.\r\n\r\nOverall the experience was great and I would definitely stay at Marylu's house again."}, {'comments': '3回目のﾊﾜｲで､ﾎﾃﾙ滞在に飽きだしていたのでこちらの宿を借りましたが､とても良かったです｡\n目の前の通りは意外と車が通り､音はそれなりに気になりましたが､60歳の父は､自然の風が適度に入ってくるﾘﾋﾞﾝｸﾞで気持ち良さそうに昼寝していましたし､浮輪やｼｭﾉｰｹﾙやﾎﾞﾃﾞｨｰﾎﾞｰﾄﾞなども借りれて､息子もとても喜んでいました｡\n徒歩5分位歩くと､有名なｶﾌｪやﾊﾝﾊﾞｰｶﾞｰｼｮｯﾌﾟ､軽食を買えるお店もあります｡また､近隣の家々も､ｵｰﾙﾄﾞﾊﾜｲ的な素敵な家が多く､歩いていてとても楽しかったです｡\n海までは､子連れだと少し距離を感じたので､自転車か車があったらﾍﾞｽﾄかもしれません｡'}, {'comments': 'This cute house was great for our group of 6! It had three bedrooms with about five beds and three couches that could also be used as beds. All in all, plenty of space! She was very responsive and the key exchange was a breeze. In addition, there were a lot of body boards and shower and beach towels that we used during our stay. Finally, the house was just a 12-15 min walk to the beach. \r\n\r\nWould stay again in the future!'}, {'comments': 'We did not meet Marylu in person, but she responded to texts very quickly. The house was just what we had expected-- informal, island style bungalow, and the location was perfect for us. The house had everything we needed for our stay, from a reasonably outfitted kitchen to beach gear. Sleeping accommodations were adequate for our large, extended family and we managed with the single bathroom. The washer and dryer were much appreciated. \r\n\r\n'}, {'comments': 'The host was very helpful, the house very cozy only problem is the washroom,(only 1) enough rm for 9 guests. Washer and dryer very handy.'}, {'comments': 'The reservation was canceled 21 days before arrival. This is an automated posting.'}, {'comments': 'The house is well located, between Diamond Head crater and Kapiolani park. The park and beach were close enough to walk several times, and there are good inexpensive places to eat a few blocks away. The night can be noisy, so bring earplugs if that bothers you, and the mornings can be bright, so bring a mask if that bothers you. We slept our family of seven easily, and cooked a lot while there with the available cookware. '}, {'comments': 'The house was exactly as it was described. Right on Campbell and in the middle and short walk to the best Acai bowl place on the island, Diamond Head Cove Health Bar on Monsarrat or if you walked the other direction you could find yourself on Kapahulu where theres a Safeway and many other stores!\r\n\r\n'}, {'comments': 'Actually this lovely home is great and our all the members, 8 adults are very satisfied and enjoyed the stay.\r\n\r\nBefore we arrived, we just a little bit worried about the size of house but it was spacious enough.\r\n\r\nIt is located only 10 minutes walking distance from the Waikiki beach.\r\nThere are the bunch of towels and surf boards and we went to beach everyday.'}, {'comments': '閑静な住宅街にある､緑に囲まれた素敵な一軒屋でした｡家から歩いて徒歩1~2分のところにﾊﾞｽ停があるので､ｱﾗﾓｱﾅｼｮｯﾋﾟﾝｸﾞﾓｰﾙへ行く際に利用しました｡ﾜｲｷｷｴﾘｱまではﾊﾞｽでも移動できますし､のんびり歩いて20分程度で着くので､ｱｸｾｽがかなり良いです｡家の中も清潔でとても居心地が良かったです｡ﾄｲﾚとお風呂が一つになっている為､大人数での利用の際には少し大変かも?\r\nまた機会があれば､是非利用したいです｡'}, {'comments': "The place was great. The host was great. Everything made sense. Exactly as advertised. I recommend Marylu's place."}, {'comments': "we had a lovely stay at marylu's cottage.  she thought of alot of extras to help make our 4 days there quite enjoyable.  our extended family of 9 found everything to be quite comfortable and accommodating.  it was a pleasure to walk in to a clean, neat place to stay."}, {'comments': "I had overall a good experience at the house. Somethings were outdated but I enjoyed my stay with my family of 8 people.  Close to Waikiki.  Only downside is no air conditioning and one bathroom.   Tv didn't work that well either"}, {'comments': 'うｰん､ﾚﾋﾞｭｰが素晴らしかったので利用したのですが､正直微妙でした…\r\nﾃﾚﾋﾞはつかないし､水道は壊れているし､ﾄｲﾚｯﾄﾍﾟｰﾊﾟｰなどの消耗品のｽﾄｯｸがないし…\r\nすべてﾎｽﾄさんに伝えたところ直したりｽﾍﾟｱを提供してもらえましたが､到着する前に準備していただきたかったです｡'}, {'comments': "Marylu's cottage is exactly as described. She is so welcoming and helped with check-in and some wifi issues. She even provided some delicious welcome favors to begin our stay ( the chocolates and coffee were amazing). The home is right on the busy street of Campbell and since there isn't any a/c, windows must be open for fresh air. There is a lot of street noise, but It is usually noisy anywhere in the hotel zones. Everything was walking distance Rainbow drive in, several stores and restaurants. We would park at the Honolulu Zoo and walk over to the beach from there every day. Wifi is available for those who need it. Make sure to go to Sweet E's for the best brunch as its close by to the home as well. "}, {'comments': 'This cottage was perfect for our week-long stay in Honolulu!  Close to plenty of action without being immersed in the bustle. The house itself has three bedrooms and could easily sleep seven adults comfortably. We would stay here again next time!'}, {'comments': 'It was super easy to deal with Marylu. The home was perfect and location even better. We will return :)'}, {'comments': 'The host left some coffee and local snacks for us, which was really nice.  The house was very spacious and clean.  The furniture is a bit dated but comfortable.  \r\n\r\nWhat takes a bit of getting use to is the noise.  Because there is no centralized air, most of the windows are open to circulate the air, which also brings in the noise from the busy street.'}, {'comments': 'The host canceled this reservation 10 days before arrival. This is an automated posting.'}, {'comments': 'Beautiful house, walking distance to the beach and plenty of beds! We had a few of us meeting in Hawaii for a wedding and this house suited us perfectly. '}, {'comments': 'Comfortable accommodations and great location. Highly recommend.'}, {'comments': 'We had a very enjoyable stay. Marylu was very responsive. There is quite a bit of road noise, as the house is on a main street. We recommend bringing earplugs if the sound cars and trucks at night will keep you awake. The house was large enough for 6 adults and a child. Very comfortable! Walking distance to the beach! '}, {'comments': 'Great location with easy access to waikiki and the all around island. Marylu was very helpful answering all our questions. \r\nHouse was a little old however great to have separate living/ sleeping areas.We had a fantastic time.\r\n'}, {'comments': 'We had a wonderful time during staying .\r\non first and 2nd day, we had difficulty to find a parking space by the house for my car , but later days are OK. The street traffic noise was loud, and need time to usd to it.\r\n\r\n\r\n'}, {'comments': 'The location is good, especially if you have a car.\r\nThe house is basic but comfortable. Good if you are looking for a place for a small group'}, {'comments': 'Felt like home, this place had everything you could think of. Super close to everything. '}, {'comments': 'Great place, well-stocked kitchen, amazing location that is near everything. Comfortable beds, lots of towels, extra blankets. The ceiling fans and open windows did a great job of keeping us cool. It is in a residential neighborhood but the street is used often, especially early morning and late afternoon. '}, {'comments': 'Very good location, although beds were quite uncomfortable. not really 3 bedrooms (1 room is very small converted from a laundry) you would struggle to sleep 8 here.\n\n'}, {'comments': "Very cosy and comfortable and in a good location we had a great time while staying at Marylu's."}, {'comments': 'D.C.'}, {'comments': 'Big enough for a party of 5, despite a single bathroom. Quite well located with bus lines very close. Very quite in the evening and good communication with Marylu. The cleaning was not perfect (some dust ball behind doors).'}, {'comments': 'Nice place and host, cool garden with bbq, very close to waikikibeach, but a very noisy street in the morning, no air conditioning and a big cockroach in the bathroom. The third room is very small we planed to sleep in it with two people but was forced to be 3 in the bigger room.'}, {'comments': 'The location within 15 minutes easy walk to the beach was fantastic.\nSimilar easy walk to Safeway and local restaurants was handy.\nThe kitchen was well appointed.  Only disappointment was the traffic noise at night.'}, {'comments': "House had all amenities and great location but it's on a busy street so it's very noisy but that didn't bother us. The house has only ceiling fans and didn't realize weather was very humid so very uncomfortable to sleep in the rooms. There are no window AC or cooler in the house."}, {'comments': 'assolutamente raccomandabile'}, {'comments': 'The house is well located and offers everything you need for a stay with a group. The only things that you should be prepared of is that the third room is only comfy for 1 person and that the street is very noise since thats a bus route. But if you have earplugs you can sleep there. Mahalo Marylu for everything :)'}, {'comments': 'Great location for beach/hikes/Waikiki. Spacious common area. Would have been nice to have a/c, but not too bad with fans on. Great for a group trip.'}, {'comments': '最高の旅行になりました｡'}, {'comments': 'Great location, close to beach and shopping.'}, {'comments': "Without air conditioning it is too hot to sleep.  It's almost a mile walk to the beach."}, {'comments': "The house may be outdated and on a busy street but the location is ideal. Close to Waikiki Beach, freeway and groceries like Safeway and Walmart. If you plan on doing some cooking, check what's in the cupboards and refrigerator first because they're well stacked with spices and other items that are useful. The washer and dryer came in handy too. "}, {'comments': 'It was a cozy, island style place.  It had most of the amenities you needed.  Would have been better if it had air conditioning but overall a nice place. '}, {'comments': 'The location of the cottage is ideal if you want to go to Waikiki beach or even for a walk on Diamond Head. I recommend Marylu who is reactive and reliable.'}, {'comments': 'The location is good, not far to walk to Waikiki beach area. The house is quite dated but had everything we needed. Marylu was great and left coffee and chocolates for when we arrived, communication was superfast.'}, {'comments': '電気が切れていたのが残念でした｡\n立地条件は良かった｡\n外でﾊﾞｰﾍﾞｷｭｰは狭くて暗いので､できませんでした｡\n男同士なら､問題無く､快適なﾗｲﾌができると思います｡'}, {'comments': '立地条件は最高です｡\nただ､ﾘﾋﾞﾝｸﾞの電気が切れていて､ﾛｳｿｸで対応しました｡\n冷蔵庫もあまり､冷えなかったです｡\n清潔感はｲﾏｲﾁでした｡\n男だけなら､気にならない程度だと思います｡\n後､蚊が多い為､蚊取線香で対応しました｡'}, {'comments': 'Great location.'}, {'comments': 'The house is extremely dated, however, excellent communication and great location make it a good place to stay if you are looking for an affordable place within walking distance of downtown.'}, {'comments': 'Good place'}], 'score': 0.695408284664154}
{'name': 'Spacious private 2BR with Backyard Williamsburg', 'neighborhood_overview': '', 'property_type': 'Apartment', 'bedrooms': 2, 'address': {'street': 'Brooklyn, NY, United States', 'suburb': 'Williamsburg', 'government_area': 'Williamsburg', 'market': 'New York', 'country': 'United States', 'country_code': 'US', 'location': {'type': 'Point', 'coordinates': [-73.94884, 40.70778], 'is_location_exact': False}}, 'reviews': [{'comments': 'It is in a really great location and Lawrence makes you feel super welcome and comfortable.\r\nThe place is really clean and tidy. A great place to stay for either a few days or an extended time in New York.\r\n\r\n'}, {'comments': "Lawrence is a great host. He was there when we needed him, and quick to reply. The place is great. Close to transportation to the city. Everything was great when we arrive, free parking around the corner between Thursday's- Sunday's. I recommend this place to anyone coming to New York"}, {'comments': 'Lawrence was a great host!  He checked up with us to make all was well; he \r\neven left us a bottle of wine to enjoy!    The apartment was very clean and the linens were fresh and fluffy! We will be back! '}, {'comments': 'Lawrence was a great host. He was available when needed and answered any questions or requests. The place was clean and very comfy. Will definitely book again.'}, {'comments': 'Lawrence is a fantastic host and place is everything advertised\n'}, {'comments': "The appartment is big enough to accomodate 4 people. We had 2 rooms with 2 double beds. Large living room with lots of room to have breakfast all together at the same table. A kitchen fully furnished, bathroom with towels and everything you should expect from a hotel. The place is nicely decorated, clean, and there are many lights in different places, so you can create a cozy atmosphere and feel like being home. Lawrence is also a very kind and caring person. He's very helpful so you don't have to worry about details during your stay in NYC. The neighborhood is calm, you won't be scared about coming home late at night. There are restaurants, coffe shops and groceries all around. You can easily get there by feet, and also transportation is not far. Visit the original Williamsburg. It's a 15 minutes walk but it's worth all the shopping, restaurants and coffe shops you need. You can also visit the artists area that is very close. Beautiful graffitis decorate the buildings walls, music gear shops, live bars, vintage clothing, tattoo studios, and hand crafted items shops"}, {'comments': 'My daughter stayed at Lawrence place , she was so happy , she keep telling me how cool and convenient is the neighborhood, and how sweet and helpful was Lawrence .\nThe appartement is great. \nI will definitely recommend.\nThank you'}, {'comments': "Lawrence's apartment is a perfect base from which to explore Brooklyn or further afield in NYC. He's a great host too, very friendly and welcoming on arrival with lots of great local tips and advice. Highly recommended."}, {'comments': "Lawrence was a fantastic host. Very attentive to any request. I don't think I waited more than a few minutes for any reply and he would go out of his way to improve me and my family's comfort.\nThe place is spotless. There is certainly limited light since it is on the lower ground floor but due to the location, comfort and value, I would recommend this spot. "}, {'comments': "Our stay at Lawrence's was really good, he was very helpful and went out of his way to accommodate us.  The basement flat is in a good location for getting the Manhattan and the rest of Brooklyn.  The kitchen is well equipped and it is very cosy. There was five of us which is probably the maximum for staying comfortably but you could make 6 work I'm sure."}, {'comments': 'Nous avons passé une semaine à 5 en famille chez Lawrence. Tout a été parfait. Le logement correspond à la description et avons été très bien reçus. Lawrence est un hôte très sympa et très serviable pour tous renseignements et aide nécessaire. Tout le voyage était super.'}, {'comments': 'Lawrence was amazing and made sure my friends and family were super comfortable!! The place was very nice and made us feel like we were right at home. The location was great too! 5 stars for sure!'}, {'comments': 'Positives:  Roomy, clean, quiet, convenient, host is responsive (attempted to fix WIFI even though traveling overseas)\nNegatives: slow WIFI  (unable to access from bedroom), single ply toilet paper, occasional noise from people walking upstairs, no windows (basement unit), uneven floor (undulations)'}, {'comments': "Lawrence est très accueillant, agréable et prends soin de ses hôtes. Tout était très propre et très fonctionnel. Tout est facile et à disposition dans cet appartement. \nLe quartier n'est cependant pas animé il faut prendre le métro qui est à 10 min à pied. (Assez facile de rejoindre manhattan avec la ligne L) Ou marcher environ 25 min pour rejoindre Bedford avenue pour y trouver tous les restaurants, bars et quelques boutiques. \nMerci à Lawrence pour son accueil et ses bonnes intentions. "}, {'comments': "Our stay was perfect. The apartment was very clean and comfortable. Lawrence is a fantastic host; he was very attentive and helpful. The apartment is close to a number of subway lines. You'll find plenty of restaurants, bodegas, and full service laundromat nearby."}, {'comments': "We had a great time staying at Lawrence's place. It's in a great location in Brooklyn. There's a lot to do in the neighborhood, and there's easy access to public transportation. \n\nThe place was very clean, with a lot of space! Like others have mentioned, there aren't many windows as it's a basement apartment but that was totally fine with us, since NY gets very hot in the summer and the place was nice and cool. Of course the A/C helps as well! The back patio/garden area is very charming.\n\nLawrence was a great communicator when it came to logistics, and also recommended a bunch of good places to eat nearby. \n\nOverall, it was a seamless experience for us and I highly recommend it!"}, {'comments': 'Affordable, comfortable, spacious, well-equipped 2 bedroom basement suite. Cool, quiet residence that was nice to come home to after the bustle of Manhattan, especially during the summer heat. Host was available and very helpful.'}, {'comments': 'We had a great stay!'}, {'comments': 'It was a pleasure to stay at this apartment. The location is in Williamsburg and very close to main roads and local stations, allowing access to direct route to major parts of NYC. There are many good eateries and locations close by for wandering and exploring. The apartment is very modern with a lovely design, it is spacious and is very nice for relaxing and has all facilities that one would needed while staying in New York. I would highly recommend staying here!\n'}, {'comments': 'Lawrence is a great airbnb host, gracious hospitality combined with a friendly attitude, perfect combination!'}, {'comments': "Staying at Lawrence's place was like visiting a cousin from New York ! He was very helpful and kind to us. The appartment was comfortable enough for a family, the kitchen very well equipped and the little garden really cute !\nPerfect place to come to visit New York : subway close, neighborhood peaceful with lots of restaurants and shops all around. We recommend it !"}, {'comments': "This place was amazing! Lawrence was very nice and caring. Great location if you're planning on taking the train into Manhattan. Can't wait to stay there again!"}, {'comments': "Lawrence was a really great host, the communication was very good and he always had time for our questions. He helped us plan our trip and gave us really good recommendations. We even could make use of his bicycle. His Airbnb was clean, everything was nicely set up. There was nothing that we've missed. The garden was wonderful, we even enjoyed  drinking our good-morning-coffee there. We highly recommend Lawrence and his Airbnb!"}, {'comments': 'Lovely apartment. We were a family of 5 adults and were very comfortable. It had everything that we needed. Beds and sofa bed very comfortable. Quiet location but walking distance to train, restaraunts, bars etc Very clean and comfortable. Nice back garden. Well equipped. There were some food and drink necessities available which was a nice surprise. The apartment was bigger than what I had imagined. Great Wi-Fi and TV. Lawrence is a very responsive host and is helpful in every way. I highly recommend this accommodation and host.'}, {'comments': '5 Star all the way..would recommend Lawrence and his place to anyone! You wont be disappointed'}, {'comments': 'Lawrence was a great host and went out of his way to ensure our stay was as perfect as possible! His suggestions on places to visit and travelling around both Brooklyn and NYC were really helpful! The apartment was perfect for us and allowed us to travel in and out of manhattan without any issues, two very local subway stations to choose from! This apartment is a perfect base to explore Brooklyn and NYC, I would highly recommend the apartment and Lawrence as a host! Will definitely go back!'}, {'comments': 'Very nice stay! Lawrence was very flexible with everything. The place was clean and also surprisingly large and had more than enough space for me and four friends.'}, {'comments': 'Great apartment. Spacious and well equipped. Really close to both the L, M and J trains to Manhattan. Some nice bars and restaurants around the immediate area too. Lawrence was really helpful and easy to keep in touch with during our stay.'}, {'comments': "Even though the reviews we read on Lawrence's apartment were very strong, our stay was even better than we thought. The apartment was clean, tidy, comfortable with everything we needed, and in a great location. Close to transport links and easy walking distance to bars, restaurants and cafes. \nLawrence and Angela were super super helpful. They didn't impose on us at all, but gave plenty of advice and tips on local sights and restaurants. You really couldn't ask for better hosts. A lovely couple. \nWe 100% recommend this apartment. A great experience"}, {'comments': "This place offers bang for the buck. True, it's a basement apartment with a funky layout, but the space is perfect for a family or a couple of friends. The location couldn't be better, right in Williamsburg--walkable to anything you could want. Lawrence is an AWESOME host. I had told him in passing that it was my friend's birthday we were celebrating, but he had put a bottle of sparkling wine waiting in the refrigerator for us when we arrived. He was very helpful but not overbearing or pushy, giving us the right amount of space while making himself available. You CANNOT GO WRONG trying out this place!"}, {'comments': 'Lawrence’s place is perfect. The best location, in the middle of Williamsburg, so close to Manhattan by train or subway. The apartment was clean and totally equipped. Lawrence was always ready to help us with the best tips. We spent ten lovely and unforgettable days there.'}, {'comments': 'The place is great. Me and four friends stayed there 3 nights. The apartment was easily big enough for 6.\n\nThe location is great - close to all the main bars in Williamsburg and very easy to get to Manhattan (8 minute walk to the Met station)\n\nLawrence was a great host and kept in touch during our stay and was flexible. A great host. Thanks for having us\n\nWould highly recommend this apartment'}, {'comments': 'Lawrence was very prompt, accommodating and provided a lot of great recommendations for things in the area. The space had plenty of room, and was super convenient location to multiple subway lines and restaurants.'}, {'comments': "This was a good choice and I recommend it. It's really, really clean, and so even though it's a basement it doesn't feel creepy. The location is great. It was very quiet but still close to so much. We had tons of options within a 4-5 block radius. Also, Lawrence was more than happy to offer us suggestions. The check-in was very easy and smooth and Lawrence was immediately responsive to all our requests. He had also stocked the kitchen with bottled water and beer for us, which I thought was so nice! He was very concerned that we have a good stay. The only couple of things I might say that I wish were different were that one, we couldn't control the heat ourselves and it made climate control a little challenging sometimes (we had to text or call Lawrence to change it for us), and two, the internet was kind of spotty (probably normal for a basement apartment). But neither of things were major issues and I would definitely stay there again. Thank you Lawrence for being such a lovely host!"}, {'comments': 'Superbe appartement comme sur les photos chambres très spacieuse et Lawrence est au top avec ses hôtes pleins de bon conseil très arrangeant il ne manque rien même jusqu au parapluie !!! Bise Lawrence nous conseillons +++'}, {'comments': 'Lawrence was an amazing host. Really fast communication and always on hand to offer recommendations.\n\nThe flat is lovely. 2 huge beds and a very comfortable sofa bed with memory foam mattress. It was an excellent base for us, very easy to get into Manhattan to do all the touristy things.\n\nWould highly recommend staying here. Perfect for small groups or families'}, {'comments': 'Me and my family spend seven days in Lawrence apartment. The kids loved it and so did we. Good space for for us and nice kitchen. Williamsburg fun place to explore and 20 mins to Manhattan.\nGreat week and Lawrence is a very good host. Would love to come back.'}, {'comments': "This apartment is a lovely space that's close by to a number of restaurants and delis. There are 3 subway stations within walking distance, making it easy to explore both Brooklyn and Manhattan. Some hot water pipes run through the ceiling of the apartment which can make it quite warm, but otherwise it's a comfortable place to stay."}, {'comments': 'Lawrence es un anfitrión de lujo! Reservamos el lugar un mes antes y unos días antes de viajar ya estuvimos en contacto con el y nos dio recomendaciones de lugares para comer o salir por la noche. Sus especificaciones para llegar al departamento fueron excelentes y siempre estuvo atento a lo que necesitábamos antes y durante nuestra estadía. El lugar es tal cual como lo ven en las fotos, habitaciones amplias y super cómodo para estar en grupo y compartir. En ubicación super bien, caminando eran como a 8min del metro que llevaba al centro de todo, o bien en taxi o uber también era cerca sobretodo si se manejan en grupo no es caro. Muchísimas gracias a nuestro super anfitrión Lawrence! Recomendado 100%  ❤'}, {'comments': 'Great place due to\n- close to communication\n- close to nightlife\n- very clean\n- better than the pictures\n- and very important, caring host that checked in often enough to ensure everything was alright. Gave also great tips on where to eat/drink etc.\n\nWould stay there again.'}, {'comments': 'If there is any doubt in your mind in booking this Airbnb, Cast it out now. Lawrence’s place spectacular. He was a wonderful host. There is absolutely nothing that can be said about this place and Lawrence. If you do not book, you surely will miss out. Much better than staying at a hotel.'}, {'comments': 'Lawrence was a great host during our recent trip to NYC. The apartment was in a great location and was extremely clean.  He made suggestions to local places, checked-in frequently, and responded to any questions we had in a timely manner. My one (Website hidden by Airbnb) of the mornings the upstairs tenant was being extremely loud from 4a-8a, which kept us up. Other than that, the warmth in the apartment was relieved by opening the front and back windows. He accommodated our check-in and check-out times, which made our stay and weekend that much more enjoyable. Would highly recommend staying with Lawrence. We will surely be back!'}, {'comments': 'Very comfortable and spacious apartment. Extremely suitable for families.'}, {'comments': 'Lawrence was beyond helpful. He replied to every message at the speed of lightning and showed the utmost care for that our stay was perfect. For example, we were in need of an iron and he did not even offer but insisted he would bring one the very same evening. He also wrote us an extensive list of local attractions, which was super helpful. The area itself is really cool and the apartment is close to several subways. I recommend Lawrence and his place one hundred percent.'}, {'comments': 'Excellent host! Great with recommendations. Perfect space that’s central in Brooklyn.'}, {'comments': 'This was a lovely space, very clean and comfortable. Lawrence was very helpful and even went out of his way to let us know there were umbrellas available when the weather turned to rain. We will be back!!'}, {'comments': 'We loved staying at Lawrence’s place. Spacious (it even has a backyard!), well-appointed with modern decor, and very conveniently located to one of the hippest neighborhoods in the city. Lawrence was very prompt to respond to any questions we had. I would highly recommend staying here during your visits to NYC/Brooklyn.'}, {'comments': 'L appartement de Lawrence est bien situé facile d accès à Manhattan par le métro. Il est cosy, fonctionnel et très propre.Lawrence est très attentionné envers ses hôtes et réactif dans ses réponses. Nous le recommandons'}, {'comments': 'Perfect location'}, {'comments': 'Lawrence was a great host. The apartment was clean and in a good location. Easy access to transportation, dining, and nightlife. We really enjoyed our stay.'}, {'comments': 'The place was excellent close to many restaurants and metro stations, we were there for 5 days and it was great.'}, {'comments': 'From the beginning we felt very welcome at Lawrence place. He was a great host with a lot of good tips. The appartment was very clean and comfortable with a lovely shared garden, comfy beds and all equipment you need. We loved the peaceful neighboorhood in Williamsburg. A welcome contrast and break with busy Manhattan. We look forward to stay with Lawrence in the near future! Thanks again for the great week, Lawrence! '}, {'comments': 'Wonderful little place in a great neighborhood. Lawrence was an amazing host and all around kind person. My family of four was quite comfortable and we had everything we needed and more. Thanks again Lawrence!'}, {'comments': 'Lawrence is a great host and accommodated us very well.'}, {'comments': 'Lawrence a été présent dés la réservation. Par la suite il a toujours été prompt à répondre aux interrogations. L’accueil au logement a été parfait. Le logement est beau propre, fonctionnel. Les lits sont confortables et il est appréciable d’avoir la Wifi. A 8 minutes de marche se trouve le métro et 15 minutes plus tard vous accédez à toutes les activités que vous offrent cette ville. \nLe séjour a été parfait et je conseille ce logement. Si je dois revenir aucun doute que je ferai le nécessaire pour retourner chez lawrence '}, {'comments': 'Lawrence was a wonderful and helpful host'}, {'comments': "Lawrence's house was exactly as described and convenient distance to any stations vicinity. We already miss a life in Brooklyn.."}, {'comments': "Lawrence is a great host - very fast in responding and checking, if everything is ok. He also stored our luggage on our last day, which was very helpful. The places is very spacious, but with no windows, so staying for 2 nights was just about the right amount of time. Also it's quite a walk towards the subway, but in a quiet neighbourhood. "}, {'comments': "Nous n'avons jamais été reçu à ace autant d'attentions. Lawrence et sa famille sont adorables. Discrets mais toujours disponibles. Cet appartement a un petit jardin partagé ou le petit déjeuner du matin est un luxe au cœur de Brooklyn.\nOu bien pour la bière du soir, bien fraîche. \n\nNous avons eu un pb personnel, et lawrence nous a aidé avec beaucoup d'humanité. Merci à lui.\n\nL'appartement est idéalement placé pour profiter des quartiers de brooklyn, street art, petits commerces et d'une ambiance très hipster.\n\nUne liste de petits resto est proposée, nous en avons faits deux, Top !!\nC'est un hôte de bon goût.\n\nDu williamsburg authentique. \nJe recommande vivement. Et c'est peu dire. "}, {'comments': 'Lawrence is very gracious and attentive to all inquiries and requests.'}, {'comments': 'Perfect host. Very cool and flexible. Location near all facilities. Clean basement. Great stay!'}, {'comments': 'Lawrence’s place is very well located, close to a range of bars and restaurants. He was an attentive host and had some great recommendations for things to do while in New York. For a basement apartment, the place felt surprisingly airy and access to the garden was a plus.'}, {'comments': 'Host is responsive and hospitable. Great location! Cool space.'}, {'comments': 'Lawrence is a genuine, friendly and very hospitable host. He enabled us to check in early and provided some fabulous information and tips about the surrounding area and NY. The apartment is in a great location and is clean - our only issue was the noise from the upstairs apartments that occurred every night during sleeping hours. If not for the ongoing noise issues (which Lawrence endeavoured to address for us) that didn’t suit our family (inc toddler), this would have been the perfect apartment. If you don’t mind noise/use to it or sleep heavy, then you’ll love this place.'}, {'comments': 'This Williamsburg apartment really fit our needs and Lawrence is a great host! He provided amenities such as water, coffees, towels, dishware, and an extra set of keys. He also gave great recommendations! \n\nThe apartment is in a great location and surrounded by many restaurants, delis, and convenience stores. It was about a 10 min walk to the G and L trains. It is a basement apartment so those with a lot of luggage or sensitive to stairs should take note. It’s only a few steps but is tight in typical Brooklyn fashion. The apartment itself is spacious, with 2 bedrooms, a large living/dining area with a bed in it, a bathroom, kitchen, and patio space. We didn’t use the patio space much because it seemed shared. The kitchen is also a bit separate from the rest of the place in the back of the apartment which made the space feel large. We loved the open floor open of the living/dining room. \n\nOne thing to note was that due to the lack of windows (basement apartment), there was very little air flow and at times the apartment felt stuffy. Lawrence provides an AC unit and you can keep one of the doors unlocked to let in air, but the AC wasn’t sufficient during our stay. Thankfully we weren’t home for long periods, but with 6 of us in the space it got warm.\n\nOverall, we really enjoyed our stay in this Williamsburg apartment! Lawrence, thank you so much for being a great host!'}, {'comments': 'Lawrence was great,\nHelped with the check in and with storing our languages after we checked out.\nhe also had great tips about the area.'}, {'comments': 'Absolutely wonderful first Airbnb experience!'}, {'comments': 'We had a wonderful stay with Lawrence. The apartment was clean, quiet, and large—perfect for a small group. We didn’t use the backyard but we did love being so close to so much in Brooklyn. We loved how the main space was laid out, surprising for a basement unit! We would definitely stay there again!'}, {'comments': 'Lots of room.'}, {'comments': 'Lawrence’s apartment was perfect in every way for our family stay - it was incredibly clean, spacious and comfortable with everything we could possibly need for our short stay. Lawrence himself was the perfect host - friendly and attentive without being at all intrusive. The apartment is ideally situated for easy access to Manhattan using the Subway, and there is a huge array of really cool places to eat and hang out locally. I just wish we’d had a little longer to explore Brooklyn itself and check out a few more of Lawrence’s wonderful recommendations!'}, {'comments': 'I had a very nice stay'}, {'comments': 'amazing stay, great location.'}, {'comments': "This place has the three C's: clean, comfortable, and close to everything great in Brooklyn. You're only steps away from great Williamsburg bars and restaurants, and the G, M, and L lines will deliver you to the rest of what NYC has to offer.\n\nLawrence was a perfect and attentive host. From the pain free check-in and check-out process, great restaurant tips, to the complimentary bottle of wine - you could not ask for more. Since the place wasn't booked on our last day, he even extended our check-out, no questions asked. That's what I call hospitality. \n\nIf you need multiple, comfortable beds, spotless facilities, and want to see the best of Brooklyn, you won't find better accommodations. I can't recommend this place enough."}, {'comments': 'Nous avons passé un séjour très agréable à New York chez Lawrence. \nLe logement est idéalement placé, proche de plusieurs stations de métro et de commerces. De plus, l’équipement proposé est complet et le logement très propre. \nLawrence est aussi très serviable et n’hésitera pas à répondre à la moindre de vos questions et à vous conseiller pour votre visite de New York. \nJe recommande ce logement.'}, {'comments': 'This place was perfect for a weekend away with friends! Check-in was super simple and the location was outstanding. I would definitely stay here again.'}, {'comments': 'We, a group of two couple, stayed in the basement for a week.\napartment: was cleaned, no windows (basement), spacy\nlocation: close to several subways, coffee-shops  and more\ncommunication/hosting: lawrence is a nice guy and had always a helping hand and recommendations\n\nthe basement is not perfectly heated (sometimes too hot, too cold and really dry air), and there are no windows. for one/two nights a really good place to stay!'}, {'comments': 'Lawrence was very helpful and was available for anything we needed help with. He gave us suggestions for good restaurants in the area as well. The apartment was very spacious, especially for New York and was only a short walk away from some cool spots in Williamsburg. The apartment gets a bit warm but there is AC in one of the bedrooms and in the living room. I would recommend this place to anyone looking for a sweet basement apartment in the area.'}, {'comments': 'Clean, cozy, very centric.'}, {'comments': 'This is a very special Airbnb. It gave us an opportunity to spread out in a comfortable and large apartment for a family reunion. I loved the detail that Lawrence put into decorating the space. The beds were so nice. I also appreciated the places for hanging and storing clothes. Lawrence was so helpful before and during our stay.'}, {'comments': 'The space is better than what the pictures show. It can get very warm because of the space being close to the boiler but I ultimately had no problem with it. Lawrence is easy to communicate with and responsive which makes him a great host. We had an issue with the sink and he came in no time to fix it. So if you stay here you do not have to worry about an unhelpful host.'}, {'comments': "Très bel appartement à proximité de plusieurs stations de métro pour rejoindre Manhattan. Propreté irréprochable, ce qui est très important pour nous ! Lawrence est disponible et à l'écoute, il donne de très bons conseils. Prévoir d'avoir un plus chaud que la normal à l'intérieur (en hiver en tout cas). Bien équipé et fonctionnel, bien placé... on recommande !"}], 'score': 0.6948082447052002}